A maiden over. Wide outside off, this is left alone.
Shorter and on leg, this is pulled towards backward square leg for one.
Back of the length, slightly shorter, Mushfiqur Rahim leans back a bit and leaves it towards the keeper.
Change of length, fuller one this time, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it towards mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Shorter and on leg, Taijul Islam ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT! A shorter one again on leg stump, Taijul Islam gets stuck in two minds and puts his bat in the end. The ball hits the glove and goes off towards Niroshan Dickwella who does no mistake. Sri Lanka finally get the 8th wicket. This partnership was frustrating them to no end and is finally broken on 49. Sri Lanka would have dreamt of keeping the opposition to around a score of 300, but now, 350 looks on the cards. For all the effort Asitha Fernando has put into bowling the short ball, he finally gets some reward for it.
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Back of the length and on leg, Khaled Ahmed blocks it towards short leg.
On a length and on middle, Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it away.
Fuller and on leg, this is flicked towards square leg.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it towards mid-wicket and looks for the single but Khaled Ahmed is not aware to the opportunity there.
Goes straight down the middle, this is blocked out.
FOUR! On a length and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim smashes it through covers for a boundary. A brilliant cover drive from Mushfiqur Rahim.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's nine down now. Back of the length and on off, Khaled Ahmed tries to shield it but gets an outside edge. The ball goes towards Niroshan Dickwella who takes a comfortable catch. Khaled Ahmed departs for a duck and Sri Lanka get their ninth wicket. Fernando is now in with a chance of a five-wicket haul as well.
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Wide down the leg side, Ebadot Hossain leaves it. Wide called.

NOT OUT! Back of the length and on off, Ebadot Hossain tries to block it but misses. A loud appeal from Niroshan Dickwella and the finger goes up. Ebadot Hossain goes upstairs. Ultra Edge shows that there was no bat involved. Review retained and the Bangladesh innings is still alive.
On a length and outside off, Ebadot Hossain leaves it alone.
Back of the length, slightly shorter, this is defended towards short leg.
Change of line and length, fuller this time, Ebadot Hossain blocks it out.
A bouncer on leg, Ebadot Hossain fumbles a bit and gets his bat on it. The ball goes towards slip and short of the fielder.
Fuller and outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it out.
On a length and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim tries for a cheeky scoop over the keeper but the ball hits the lower part of the bat and just falls short off the keeper around leg gully.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Fuller and outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim cuts it through point and gets a single.
On middle, this is blocked out.

Fuller and outside leg, Ebadot Hossain leaves it and the keeper misses it as well. The ball races towards long stop. They get a couple of byes. It could be a chance of a run out but Asitha Fernando, the fielder at long stop with a poor throw allows the batters to pick up two.
On middle, this is defended solidly.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Fuller and outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim tries to cut it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it towards mid off.
Darts it towards leg, Mushfiqur Rahim tries to flick it but hits his pads.
Fired in fuller and wider outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim tries to play it but couldn't. Wide called and the bowler seems disappointed with the call.
On a length and on middle, Mushfiqur Rahim tries to cut it but gets a bottom edge towards short third man who is well inside the inner ring.
Shorter one on middle, Ebadot Hossain ducks under it.
On a length and on middle, Ebadot Hossain blocks it away.
A bouncer on middle, Ebadot Hossain tries to block it but misses.
Shorter one on leg, Ebadot Hossain ducks this one and leaves it towards the keeper.
Similar to the last one, Ebadot Hossain ducks this one as well and lets it go.
Shorter and outside off, Ebadot Hossain leaves it alone.
Fuller and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim sweeps it towards backward square leg.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended towards mid on.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
On off, this is guided towards covers for one. Once again Sri Lanka just allowing that easy single to Rahim towards the end of the over
Fuller and on off, this is blocked towards silly point.
Fuller and outside off with a little turn, Ebadot Hossain tries to block it but misses.
Tossed up on leg, this is blocked out solidly.
Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim uses his feet and smashes it towards long off. No runs taken.
On middle, blocked out.
On a length outside leg, Mushfiqur Rahim gives a little cut and the ball races towards third man. A couple of runs taken.
Fuller and outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim cuts it towards backward point. A couple of runs taken.

Fuller and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single. Ohh, it's a no ball.  The players were about to leave for the break but they are called back, bizarre but now de Silva has a chance to bowl to the tailender.
Fuller and outside off, Ebadot Hossain block it towards gully. That will be Lunch for Day 2.
On a length, drifted into leg stump. Rahim eases it through wide mid on and denies the run.
On middle, kept out.
Flighted this time, on off. Rahim strides out to defend.
Gives it a lot more air and bowls it on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim pushes it back to the bowler.
The field comes in and Jayawickrama tosses it up on middle. Rahim looks to go big but mistimes it towards mid on.

In the air...safe! This is tossed up outside off, Rahim looks to go big over extra cover but ends up slicing it over the man at backward point. The fielder chases it down and Rahim just takes the single. He will retain strike for the next over.
Length ball, around middle and leg. Rahim tucks it away to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! This is fuller and down leg, Mushfiqur Rahim looks to flick but seems to have got it off the pads. Niroshan Dickwella dives down to his left and pouches it nicely. Sri Lanka are certain that they have got their man. The keeper cannot believe that the umpire hasn't given it and Dimuth Karunaratne does go for the review. Ultra Edge shows that there's a flat line as the ball goes past the bat and Rahim survives.
Full and straight, driven straight to mid on.
On a good length, around off. Rahim goes back and across to ease it through for point for a run.
This is well outside off and Ebadot Hossain lets it through to the keeper.
Rajitha switches to around the wicket for the final delivery and digs in a short one on leg stump. Hossain ducks under it well.
Premeditated from Mushfiqur Rahim. Rahim looks to reverse sweep and Jayawickrama just floats it down leg, Rahim gets it down to deep square leg but denies the run.
Tossed up, on off. Rahim uses his feet and heaves it down to long off.
On middle, driven towards wide long on. No run again.
Fuller and on off, Rahim opens the face of the bat and plays it behind point for a single.
Slower through the air, around middle and leg. Hossain keeps it out on the leg side.
Jayawickrama tries to attack the pads but spills it down leg. Hossain goes for the pull shot but makes no connection.
Length ball, outside off. Rahim taps it towards deep cover.

OUT! RUN OUT! This is full and straight, Mushfiqur Rahim uses his wrists to flick it through wide mid on. Rahim looks for the second run and Ebadot Hossain responds quickly. Dimuth Karunaratne at wide long on fires in the throw towards the bowler who does well to whips off the bails really quickly. The decision is sent upstairs and the replay shows that Hossain did put in the desperate dive but his bat is on the line as the bails come off. Hossain goes and Rahim stays not out on 175 as Bangladesh get bundled out for 365!
Howout: run out (Dimuth Karunaratne / Kasun Rajitha)

Commentary: This one stays low! Not good signs for Lanka. This will now play on the batter's mind. He will be a little unsure going ahead whether to come ahead ot stay back! Length and outside off, this stays low and skids through. Fernando fails to put bat on ball.
Fails to put bat on ball again! Angled into the pads, Fernando looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
BEATEN! That is a beauty! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Fernando looks to play the original trajectory but is beaten.
Finally puts bat on ball! A good, confident stroke! Fuller and on middle, this is driven to mid off.
FOUR! Sri Lanka and Fernando are underway! Easy pickings for the opener! On the pads, this is clipped through square leg and the ball races away to the fence.

NOT OUT! That is off the pad and that is exactly why Fernando reviewed! He survives to fight another day! On the pads, Fernando looks to flick but it goes off something to the keeper. An appeal and the finger is raised. Bangladesh celebrate but that is cut short as it is a successful review by Fernando. 4 from the first over then.
Dimuth Karunaratne is off the mark now! Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Bangs it short and on middle, Fernando stands tall and defends.
Length and around off, Fernando plays it to covers.
FOUR! Bread and butter stuff for Oshada! On the pads yet again, this is worked through square leg and this one too races away. Second boundary in the 10 balls bowled so far.
Bangs this short and on middle, this is nudged around the corner for one.
A harmless nut to end! Down the leg side, Dimuth looks to flick but misses.
Shorter and on middle, Fernando stands tall and blocks it out.
A quick run! On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to push at it, it goes off the inner half towards the leg side. Oshada wants a run but is sent back.
Well bowled! Length and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne shoulders arms to this one.
Another waste of a delivery! Well wide outside off, left alone.
Yet another nut outside off, not played at.
Good length and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Solid! Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Shortish and outside off, Fernando looks to push at it, this goes more off the outer half but lands well short of the gully fielder.

That was needless from the fielder! Fuller and on off, Fernando strokes it to mid off. The fielder has a needless shy at the bowler's end. The stumps are hit but the batter is well in. It deflects away from the fielder backing up and a run is taken.
Outside off, on the fuller side. Left alone.
Yet anther nut outside off, left alone.
Angled into middle, Fernando pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length and on off, Fernando pushes it to covers.
On the stumps, Fernando shows the full face of the bat and plays it to mid on.

That takes off! Well played in the end from Fernando! Length and on off, this lands and takes off. Fernando does well to play it onto the ground. He takes one hand off the handle as he tries to fend at it.
Not a good follow up ball! Gets away with it though! On the pads, Fernando flicks it to square leg.
FOUR! Put away! Finds the gap nicely! Shorter and on off, Fernando stands tall and guides it past point. This one races away to the fence.
Good length and on off, defended.
Half an appeal but that is going down leg! Angled into the pads, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Angled into the pads, Fernando works it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Yet again a little too straight! An ambitious appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire! Angled into the pads, Karunaratne looks to flick but misses.
FOUR! Put away again! Ebadot Hossain has been way too straight and this time pays for it! On the pads, this is clipped through square leg for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Back of the length and outside off, Oshada Fernando punches it through backward point. The ball goes over the ropes for a boundary.
On a length and on leg, this is blocked out solidly.
Sticks to his length, Oshada Fernando clips it towards backward square leg. He gets a couple of runs.
On a length and on middle, quicker too, this is pushed pack towards Khaled Ahmed.
Fuller and on off, this is defended towards the mid on region.
Fuller and on leg, Oshada Fernando flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
Flatter and on off, this is blocked out towards silly point.
Flatter and on middle, Oshada Fernando eases it towards point.
On middle again, this is defended towards mid on.
Sticks to bowling it on middle, this is pushed back towards Shakib Al Hasan.
On middle again, this is eased off towards silly point.
Darts it on off, Oshada Fernando defends it to point. A maiden over from Shakib Al Hasan.
On middle, this is blocked out.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne tries to cut it but gets a lucky outside edge as the ball races towards third man for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended out.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne makes room for himself and cuts it through backward point. The ball races past the fence for a boundary.
On middle, this is eased towards the on-side.
Fuller and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne uses his feet and blocks it out. towards mid on.
Flatter and on off, this is eased off towards silly point.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again, pushed towards Shakib Al Hasan.
On a length and outside off, Oshada Fernando waits for the ball and cuts it towards third man. He finds a couple of runs.
On middle, blocked out solidly.
Flatter and on middle, Oshada Fernando goes on his backfoot and defends it firmly.
Fuller and on leg, this is defended towards short leg.
Fuller and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne whips it towards square leg and gets a couple of runs.
Darts it on middle, this is blocked out.
Similar to the last one, this is defended towards mid on.
On middle, this is pushed back towards Mosaddek Hossain.

FOUR! Goes fuller and on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne just gives a fine tickle using the pace of the ball. The ball races past the fine leg region for a boundary. This was a poor delivery from Mosaddek Hossain.
Darts it on middle, this is eased off towards mid on for one.
Flatter and on middle, this is defended back towards Shakib Al Hasan.
On middle again, Dimuth Karunaratne tries to block it but gets an outside edge as it goes towards the mid-wicket region.
Sticks to his line and length, this is defended out.
On off, Dimuth Karunaratne drives it towards covers and rotates the strike.
On a length and on middle, Oshada Fernando flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Oshada Fernando drives it past covers for a boundary. That was an excellent cover drive from Oshada Fernando.
On middle, blocked out.
Fuller and on middle, this is eased towards mid off.
Fuller and on middle again, Oshada Fernando leans forward and blocks it away.
On a length and on off, this is pushed towards mid off for one.
FOUR! A gift from Bangladesh. Fuller and on off, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it out towards mid off. The fielder tries for a direct hit but misses and the ball goes towards third man for a boundary.
This was a brilliant delivery. On a length and outside off, Oshada Fernando gets in two mids but puts his bat on the very last moment. Nothing to worry about but he gets lucky.
On middle, defended out.
On off, this is guided towards point for a brace.
On a length and outside off, this is driven towards covers for one.
Fuller and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards mid-wicket.
fuller and on middle, this is pushed towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! On a length and on off, Oshada Fernando uses his feet and drives it past covers for a boundary. This is brilliant batting from Oshada Fernando.
n a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Fuller and outside leg, Oshada Fernando attempts for a sweep but misses.

NOT OUT! Fuller and drifting onto middle. The ball spins away after pitching and Oshada Fernando tries to block it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal from Taijul Islam. The finger stays down and Bangladesh goes for a review. Ultra edge shows that no bat is involved. Ball tracking shows that the ball was pitching on the line and was just clipping the off stump. The result goes in favor of the umpire whose call was not out.
On middle, blocked out.
Fuller and outside off, Oshada Fernando drives it to the fielder on covers.
Fuller and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it back towards Shakib Al Hasan.
On middle, this is blocked out.
Fuller and on middle, this is eased towards mid off.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
On a length and on leg, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards square leg for a brace.
Goes fuller and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it out solidly.
Tossed up on middle, this is pushed back towards Taijul Islam.
FOUR! Goes full and on leg, Oshada Fernando sweeps it towards fine leg for a boundary. This was a brilliant shot.
On a length and on middle, this is blocked out solidly.
Fuller and outside off, Oshada Fernando pushes it towards covers.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the Taijul Islam.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again, defended towards the bowler.
On a length and on leg, this is flicked towards square leg for one.
Tossed up on middle, Oshada Fernando drives it towards the fielder on mid off.
On off, blocked out.

Goes fuller and on middle, Oshada Fernando uses his feet and fires it straight. Shakib Al Hasan puts his hands but couldn't catch it as it was hit with a lot of power. It would have been a brilliant catch but it is an opportunity missed by Bangladesh.
On middle, eased towards mid off.
Fuller and on middle, this is eased towards the on-side.
On a length and on middle with a slight turn, this is defended out.
Fuller and on middle, this is hit straight past the bowler for one.
On off, this is blocked out towards silly point.
Tossed up on middle, this is pushed back towards Taijul Islam.
On a length and on off, this is defended towards mid on.
Fuller and on leg, Oshada Fernando flicks it towards fine leg and gets a single.
SIX! Tossed up, on a length and on middle, Oshada Fernando uses his feet really well and lofts it over long off for a biggie. Fifty up for Oshada Fernando and he gets his fifty in style.
Flatter and outside off, Oshada Fernando leaves it alone.
On a length and on middle, this is punched towards long on for one.
Flatter and outside off, this is driven towards covers.
Fuller and on middle, this is flicked towards mid-wicket for one.
On middle, defended out.

Uppish but safe! Tossed up outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne dances down the track and looks to go over extra cover but ends up dragging it towards mid-wicket. Luckily for him, there is no fielder there, single taken.
On a length, drifted into off. Fernando blocks it out.
Slowed up, on off, just a hint of turn away from the left-hander. Fernando nudges it towards covers.
On off, blocked out.
This is on middle, Fernando works it towards short mid-wicket.
Flatter this time, at the stumps. Fernando defends it out.
On a length and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne raises arms as it goes towards the keeper.
Back of the length, Dimuth Karunaratne blocks it away.
Sticks to his line and length, this is defended towards mid off.
On middle again, this is defended out towards silly point.
Back of the length, slightly shorter, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
On a length and on middle, Oshada Fernando tucks it towards square leg for a single. That will be the tea break for Day 2.
Slower through the air, shorter and around off. Fernando backs away and pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter this time, on off. Kept out.
Fuller and on off, nicely driven past mid off for a single.
Flighted, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne steps out and flicks it uppishly towards mid-wicket.
Slowed up, on a length and close to the off pole. Karunaratne defends it out.
Drifted into middle and leg, Karunaratne goes deep in his crease and works it in front of square on the leg side for one.
Right on the money! Around the top of off, Karunaratne stays solid in defense.
This is slanted across off, Karunaratne hangs back and chops it over the jumping fielder at gully for a couple of runs. Good running.
Length, on off. Karunaratne defends it off the inner half of the bat onto the leg side.
Back of a length, around off. Karunaratne bends his back and punches it through covers for one.
Goes fuller this time, closer to the off pole. Fernando pushes it straight back to the bowler.
Brilliant stop! Back of a length, around off. Oshada Fernando punches it sweetly off the back foot but the man at covers makes a good stop and even hits the stumps at the bowler's end.
Nicely flighted, outside off. Karunaratne uses his feet and pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, fuller and on off this is driven towards the bowler.
Full and on middle, flicked straight to the man at short mid-wicket.
On a length, drifting onto the pads. Karunaratne goes on the back foot and works it towards leg gully.
Shorter this time, on off. This is just eased through covers for a single.
Floated up, around off. Fernando strides forward and pushes it out onto the off side.
This is full and down the leg side, Karunaratne misses the flick.

Huge shout for lbw, turned down! Ebadot Hossain goes full and on the pads, Karunaratne misses the flick and gets rapped on the pads. Hossain appeals but it seems to have pitched outside leg. The skipper asks the keeper, who signals the same. Well, the replay shows that it was pitching in line and it would have been curtains for Karunaratne had the review been taken, opportunity missed by Bangladesh.
Full and on the pads, clipped towards deep mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Streaky but will do. Full and wide, Oshada Fernando has a go at it and ends up slicing it past the man at backward point for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Ebadot Hossain does get a wicket afterall in this over and its a big one as well. Hossain looks up at the big screen and sees that he could have had a wicket and hence puts a bit extra behind this delivery. Good-length, at 143.9 kp and outside off. Oshada Fernando hangs back and looks to run it down to third man away from his body. No feet movement and the outside edge is taken. Najmul Hossain Shanto takes a sharp catch at first slip and Fernando has to depart after a good innings.
Howout: c Najmul Hossain Shanto b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: This is fuller and angling into off. Mendis drives it towards mid off.
Sharp chance put down! Flighted, around off and Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it straight to the man at forward short leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy has no time to react and ends up spilling it.
Flatter, on middle. Karunaratne keeps it out.
FOUR! Dragged down on leg stump, keeping a bit low. Dimuth Karunaratne gets low and swivels to pull it into the backward square leg fence.
Flatter, on middle. Karunaratne keeps it out of the back foot.
Shorter and around leg, Karunaratne flicks it off the back foot past backward square leg for a couple of runs. Leg bye signaled so it may have been just off the pads.
On off, blocked out.
Fuller and shaping into off. Mendis keeps it out.
Floated up, outside off. Kusal Mendis strokes it through covers and picks up a couple of runs to get off the mark.
A touch fuller, around off. This is kept out on the off side.
Hossain goes wider of the crease and delivers a length ball outside off. Mendis taps it towards cover-point.
Back of a length, on the fifth stump line. This is played off the back foot towards covers.
Full and straight, pushed towards mid on.
Quicker and shorter, turning in from outside off. Karunaratne rocks back and punches it through covers for a brace.
Flatter this time, on off. Karunaratne defends it out.
Flatter again, angled into off and this one keeps low. Karunaratne does well to dab it down towards backward point.
Tossed up, on off. Karunaratne takes a step ahead and works it to mid-wicket.
Drops it a little short again, turning in from around off. This is played off the back foot through extra cover for a single.
On middle, Mendis goes back and across to defend.
On a good length, around middle and leg. Karunaratne tucks it away to deep mid-wicket for one.
Good delivery. Short ball, on middle, hurries onto Kusal Mendis who tries to take it on. Mendis mistimes the pull shot badly in front of square and picks up a single.
Length ball, on middle, this is driven towards wide mid on.
Goes fuller this time, on middle and leg. Karunaratne blocks it off.
A bit too full and a bit too straight, flicked away towards the man at mid-wicket.
Attempted yorker, ends up being a low full toss on the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne clips it through mid-wicket and picks up another single.
On a length, on off, kept out.
Flatter, around off. Karunaratne pushes it through covers for a couple of easy runs.
On middle, flicked through mid-wicket for one and Karunaratne moves on to 49 now.
Short and around off, cut away towards covers.
Nicely flighted, on off. Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Drifted onto middle, solidly blocked off by Mendis.

Length ball, angled across off. Dimuth Karunaratne guides it away nicely to deep backward point for a single and that's the FIFTY for the skipper. Important knock this from Karunaratne and his team will be hoping he carries on in the same fashion.

A snorter of a delivery from Ebadot Hossain. Shorter, outside off and angled in. The ball nips away after pitching and there's sharp bounce on offer as well. Mendis has a tentative push at it but misses.
Back of a length, over middle. This one doesn't bounce much and Mendis jabs it in front of square on the leg side for one.
Around the top of off, cut away towards cover-point.

Sloppy! Back of a length, a mistimed punch off the back foot by Dimuth Karunaratne towards extra cover. Tamim Iqbal over there misses the ball completely and this allows the batters to pick up a couple of runs.
Pacy bouncer from Hossain, over leg stump. Karunaratne ducks under it.
On a length, drifted into middle. Mendis keeps it out on the off side.
Flatter, around off. Mendis plays it with the turn and off the back foot through covers for a run.
Unlucky! Taijul Islam loops it up, around off. Dimuth Karunaratne strides out looking to block but gets a leading edge well in front of short leg and Taijul cannot believe it.
On middle, nudged away leg side by Karunaratne.
This one stays low! Flatter, on off and keeping low. Karunaratne defends it out.
Floated up on middle, Karunaratne can't get it past the man at silly mid on.
Tight line on off stump, Mendis gets right behind the line to make the block.
Fullish length, angled into the pads. Mendis keeps it out towards mid on.

Just short! Khaled Ahmed comes back in and almost picks up a wicket. A length ball, shaping into middle and leg but the ball sticks a bit into the pitch. Kusal Mendis doesn't read it at all and is way too early in his shot and ends up chipping it in front of the man at short mid-wicket. Mendis looks at his bat and signals for a different bat.
Nagging length, on middle, solidly blocked off by Mendis.
Fuller and around off, Mendis shoulders arms to it. The ball dies on its way to the keeper.
Maiden over! Full and straight, pushed towards mid on.
Pitched up, around off. Karunaratne keeps it out.
This is sliding down leg, Dimuth Karunaratne gets down on one knee and sweeps it really fine. The man from leg gully chases it down and the batters come back for three.
On off, pushed away onto the off side for a single.
Islam slows it up and pulls back the length as well. Karunaratne waits for it and defends it back onto the deck.
Flatter delivery, Karunaratne initially looks to come forward but hops back to nudge it onto the leg side.
Just a tad bit short, on middle. Dimuth Karunaratne rocks back and mistimes the aerial pull shot towards deep mid-wicket. He picks up another single.
On a length and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne shoulders arms as the ball goes towards the keeper.
On a length and outside off again, this is blocked towards covers.
Fuller and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
On a length and on middle, this is guided towards on-side.
Fuller and outside leg, Kusal Mendis looks for a fine flick but misses. The keeper gets his glove on it.
On middle, blocked out solidly.
Slower one on middle, this is eased towards short leg.

FOUR! That was an effortless shot. Fuller and outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne waits for the ball, uses the pace of the ball, and guides it towards the backward point for a boundary. Ebadot Hossain with a dive to save the boundary and gets hurt. He looks in a bit of pain.
Back of the length and o leg, Dimuth Karunaratne tries to pull it but misses.
On off, defended out.

Back of the length, slightly shorter, this is blocked out.

On a length and on middle, Shakib tries to slog sweep it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal and the finger stays down. Ultra edge shows that there is no bat involved. Ball tracking shows that it was pitching outside off. The original decision stays not out.
On middle, this is eased towards square leg.

OUT! LBW! On a length and on middle, Kusal Mendis tries to block it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Bangladesh finally get their second wicket as the man, Kusal Mendis walks out for 11. Relief for Bangladesh players and they will hope to get another one before Stumps.
Howout: lbw b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: Flatter and on middle, this is eased towards silly point.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven towards covers.
On middle, blocked out.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again, defended out solidly. A wicket-maiden over for Shakib Al Hasan.
Slatter one on middle, this is eased towards mid on.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! On a length and on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne with a reverse sweep as the ball races past the backward point for a boundary. That was an effortless shot. A slight halt in play as Dimuth Karunaratne looks a bit uneasy and lies down. The physio does his job as we are good to go.
On a length and outside leg, Dimuth Karunaratne lets it go.
On middle, blocked out.
Fuller and on middle, this is flicked towards mid-wicket.
On  length and outside off, this is guided towards gully.
On middle, blocked out.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended towards silly point.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the Shakib Al Hasan.
On off, defended towards silly point.
Fuller and on middle, this is eased back towards the bowler. THAT WILL BE STUMPS FOR DAY 2.
Hossain starts off with a length ball on leg stump. Karunaratne with a stylish flick to deep mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! Cleaned up! Ebadot Hossain strikes right away and the nightwatchman departs. Perfect length, close to the off pole and nipping in and just straightening a touch. Kasun Rajitha puts out a defensive stance but completely misses the line of the ball. The ball goes on to hit the top of off stump and the stump goes flying. Hossain has his second wicket.
Howout: b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: Fuller in length, around off. Matthews defends it off the front foot.
Tighter and straighter, at good pace. Matthews turns it leg side.
Fullish length, on the fifth stump line, left alone.
Excellent finish to a productive over from Ebadot Hossain. Length, on off and at 140.9 kph. Matthews defends it out.
On a length, slower through the air and on off. Karunaratne defends it out.
A touch flatter, on middle. This is pushed back to thye bowler.
Drifted onto the pads, Karunaratne nudges it past short leg.
This is sliding onto the pads, Karunaratne tucks it away behind square on the leg side.
FOUR! Short and wide, Karunaratne rocks back and cuts it into the vacant point fence for a boundary.
Shaklib goes fuller and spears it into off stump. Karunaratne drives it straight towards mid off.
This is bowled around the hips, Angelo Mathews hops and tucks it away to fine leg for a single. Matthews is off the mark.
Hossain switches to around the wicket and angles in a full ball on off stump. Karunaratne keeps it out.
Keeps it on a fuller length, close to the off pole. Karunaratne drives it towards point.
On a good length, bit of width on offer. Karunaratne hangs back and caresses it past point for a single. The 150 is up for Sri Lanka.
A well-directed short ball from Ebadot Hossain now, over middle and Matthews ducks under it.
Good bowling from Hossain. This is short and at the body, Angelo Mathews gets cramped up and just about manages to hop and keep it down past short leg. He picks up a single.
On a length, sliding in from outside off. Matthews backs away and taps it to short cover.
On off, pushed towards short cover.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Matthews stays solid in defense.
On off, flicked away leg side.
Shorter in length, on off. Matthews plays it off the back foot towards cover-point.
This one keeps low. Shakib Al Hasan just slides it into middle and leg and the ball doesn't bounce at all. Angelo Mathews does well to keep it out. Maiden over!
Banged in short, down leg. Dimuth Karunaratne gets surprised by the extra bounce on that occasion as he ducks under it.
Another goos short ball from Ebadot Hossain. This is on middle and Karunaratne does well to keep it down onto the deck.
Goes fuller and into the channel around off, left alone by Karunaratne.
Right around the top of off, Karunaratne punches it sweetly off the back foot but can't beat the man at short cover.
Another short ball, over leg stump and this one Karunaratne is able to duck under it with a little more ease.
Brilliant follow-up delivery. Full and quick at 142.5 clicks and right at the toes as well. Karunaratne manages to flick it away towards mid-wicket. Back-to-back maidens here for Bangladesh.
A bit too close for comfort. This is on a length, close to the off pole, Angelo Mathews makes an ssured leave.
On off, blocked out.
Flatter this time, on off. Matthews defends it out.
Fuller and around off, stroked away towards covers.
This one slides on with the arm, on middle and leg. Matthews manages to keep it out on the leg side.
Another maiden. This is darted onto off stump, Matthews remains unfazed.
On a good length, around off. Karunaratne hangs back and eases it towards covers.
Shorter this time, angling across the left-hander. Karunaratne watches it zip through to the keeper.
Good pace and good carry here. Good-length, around off and Karunaratne shoulders arms to it.
Pitched up, on off. Karunaratne punches it back to the bowler.
Banged in short and over middle. Karunaratne ducks under it.
Very full and straight at 142.5 clicks, Karunaratne drives it right back past the bowlers but can't beat mid on. Yet another maiden for the hosts.
Nicely floated up, on off. Matthews blocks it out.
Slowed up, on a nagging length and around middle. Matthews goes back and across to keep it out.
On a length, around off. Blocked.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Matthews pushes it towards mid on.
Flatter this time, on off and keeping a tad low. Angelo Mathews pats it through mid off and collects a run.
On a length, around middle. Karunaratne goes back to flick it leg side but ends up mistiming it towards mid-wicket.
Pitched up, around off and at good pace again. Matthews hangs back to defend it out.
Length this time, angled into the pads. Matthews manages to keep it out in front of the man at short leg.

Peach! Ebadot Hossain goes a bit wider and angles it in on that fifth stump line. Angelo Mathews is on the back foot expecting a short one. The ball just holds its line and zips past the outside edge of Matthews' willow.
On a good length, around middle. Matthews plays it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! For once Ebadot Hossain errs in line and gets punished. This is around the hips and angling down, Matthews just tucks it away into the backward square leg fence for a welcome boundary.
Length, on off. Matthews with a back-foot punch past the diving bowler for a single towards mid on.
Short and around off, Angelo Mathews rocks back and cuts it through point. The fielder from point hunts it down and just about pulls it back in time, brilliant effort. Three runs taken.
Shorter again, around middle and leg. Karunaratne flicks it off the back foot towards square leg.
Flatter, on off, this is punched towards cover-point.
FOUR! Short and wide, Dimuth Karunaratne backs away and slaps it through the point region for a boundary.
On off, defended off the front foot.

OUT! TIMBER! Classical left-arm orthodox delivery from Shakib Al Hasan and he gets rid of the big fish. Shakib was bowling flatter and flatter but this time he gives it a good loop and bowls it around off. This is bowled from around the wicket and the rough is found. Dimuth Karunaratne is drawn forward as he looks to flick it away but gets undone in flight. The ball turns in and goes between bat and pad to crash into middle stump. Karunaratne departs after a well-made 80 and the hosts in the ascendancy now.
Howout: b Shakib Al Hasan

Fuller and on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it towards Taijul Islam. The batter was out of his crease so Taijul Islam tries for a direct hit that hits the glove of Angelo Mathews. Apologies by Taijul Islam. A slight halt in play.
Touch fuller and on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks it out solidly.

FOUR! That's is a poor delivery. He tries for a yorker but ends up bowling a low full toss, Dhananjaya de Silva uses the pace of the ball and flicks it towards backward square leg for a boundary.

FOUR! Fuller and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva gets low and creams it through covers for a boundary. That was an effortless and brilliant cover drive.
Goes full and on middle, much better from Ebadot Hossain, this is blocked out.

FOUR! A lucky one for Dhananjaya de Silva this time. Sticks to his line and length, Dhananjaya de Silva tries to block it but gets a thick outside edge, and the ball races past the third man for a boundary. This is the third boundary of the over.
Much better line and length this time, on the middle, Dhananjaya de Silva defends this one out.
Tossed up on leg, this is defended out solidly. Well, the rain gods have arrived and before the over could end and umpires call for Lunch, the players will have to go off.

On middle, this is hit on the bounce to the man at short cover.
Sliding into middle, Mathews keeps it out.
Ooh, some turn and bounce for Shakib! Looped up a bit, around off. Angelo Mathews has a tentative push at it but the ball grips and bounces, goes off the outside edge and past first slip.
Quicker delivery, on off. Kept out.
Floated up, on a length and around middle. De Silva backs away and pushes it towards mid on.
On off, de Silva strides forward to defend.
A tad shorter, coming in with the angle and on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it out.

Beaten! Brilliantly bowled from Taijul Islam. Tossed up, drifted onto middle and turns away a touch after pitching. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to get behind the line but the ball goes agonizingly past the outside edge.
On middle, solidly blocked off by de Silva.
Maiden! Flighted delivery, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva keeps it out.
Starts with a fullish delivery, outside off. Mathews hangs back and pushes it out on the off side.
Length ball, angling into middle and leg. Angelo Mathews works it towards mid-wicket and picks up a single. Also, the sun is now just peeking from in between the clouds and that's a good sign.

Close call! Hossain drifts down the leg side, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to flick it away but misses. There is a noise and the keeper goes up. Seems to have brushed the thigh pad and Bangladesh don't review it. The replay shows that there's nothing on UltraEdge, the ball missed everything.
Length again, on off. De Silva blocks it out.
On a good length, close to off. Dhananjaya de Silva punches it towards covers.
Short but not short enough to pull. This is over middle, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to swing across the line but misses. He gets hit high on the pads.
Loopy delivery, on middle. Mathews pushes it towards mid on.
Nicely tossed up and on off, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Taijul just slides this one into middle and leg, Mathews does well to get a bat on it and keep it out on the leg side.
On middle, Mathews nudges this one with soft hands towards mid-wicket.
Around middle and leg, pushed back to the bowlers.

Nicely bowled! This is just a bit shorter and quicker on middle. Angelo Mathews looks to defend off the front foot but is taken aback by the sharp turn and bounce. Matthews though manages to fend it away and it will be another maiden over for Taijul Islam.
On a length, close to the off pole. De Silva defends it out on the off side.
On the pads, tucked away to square leg.
Hossain maintains a tight line around the off pole. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it off the front foot.
Hossain goes wider of the crease and tries to angle it into the off stump. The ball is pitched just a bit too wide to trouble the batter as de Silva makes an easy leave.
Pitched up around off and angling it in. De Silva with a solid block off the front foot.
Back of a length, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva hops back to keep it out.
Drifted onto middle and leg, worked away towards wide mid on.
On middle, Mathews prods and defends it out.
Taijul gives it a good loop and drifts it into middle. Angelo Mathews looks to drive it through covers but is undone in flight and ends up getting an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, blocked out.
Nicely flighted, around off. Mathews pushes it towards short cover.
Tossed up and drifting onto middle. Mahews strides forward to defend. Three maidens on the trot now for Taijul Islam since the resumption.
On a hard length, on off. De Silva pushes it out on the leg side.
FOUR Overpitched and punished! This is a half-volley around off, Dhananjaya de Silva caresses it through extra cover and finds the fence.
A length ball, around off. Kept out by de Silva.
Fuller in length and around off. This is driven towards mid off.
Back of a length, on the fifth stump line. De Silva plays it off the back foot towards point.

Length ball, just angling down leg. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to tickle it fine but misses. There is a stifled appeal from the keeper but Bangladesh don't go for the review. The replay shows that there was no bat involved.
Flatter one around leg, Angelo Mathews pushes it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on leg, this is flicked towards mid-wicket.
On a length and on leg, Angelo Mathews leans forward and blocks it out with his pads.

Flatter one on off with a hint of turn away from the right-hander, it just deviates past the bat and goes in the hands of the keeper who tried to stump it. A loud appeal but the umpire stays uninterested.
On middle, Angelo Mathews stays in the crease and blocks it firmly.
Flatter and on off, Angelo Mathews uses his feet and blocks it out solidly.
Touch fuller and outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva tries to block it but gets an inside edge as the ball races towards backward square leg. Single taken.

Back of the length, slightly shorter, Angelo Mathews pulls it towards fine leg and gets an easy single.

On a length and on middle, this is eased off towards deep square leg for one.

Darts it on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva moves across to his leg and drives it through mid off and straight to the fielder on long off. A single taken.
Flatter and on middle, Angelo Mathews leans forward and blocks it away.

Tad fuller and on off, this is defended out solidly.
Touch fuller and on middle with a hint of swing, Angelo Mathews pushes it back towards Khaled Ahmed.
Similar to the last delivery, Outside off this time, this is again, pushed back towards the bowler.
FOUR! On a length and outside off, Angelo Mathews leans a bit and drives it through mid off. The ball races past the fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Fuller and on middle, Angelo Mathews looks to block it but gets an outside edge. The ball races past the slip fielder and towards third man for a boundary.
Flatter and on leg, quicker too, Dhananjaya de Silva flicks it towards square on the on-side for one.
On a length and on off, this is defended towards silly point.

This is a good delivery. Fuller and on middle angling it in, Dhananjaya de Silva flicks it towards backward square leg and gets a single.
Touch fuller and on off, this is worked towards mid on for one.
On off, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to drive it but hits the lower part of his bat.
FOUR! Shorter one and on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva pulls it through square leg and the ball races past the fence for a boundary.
SIX! Outside off, Angelo Mathews uses his feet and smashes it over long off for a maximum. Fifty up for Angelo Mathews and his fine series continues. He would know though only half the job is done.
On middle, this is defended towards silly point.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven towards covers for one.
Flighted one on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Flighted up on middle with a bit of turn, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to block it but misses as it goes towards the keeper. A loud appeal from the keeper but the finger stays down. Bangladesh go for a late review. Ultra Edge shows that there was a clear spike and Dhananjaya de Silva has to walk away. Bangladesh finally gets a breakthrough and Dhananjaya de Silva walks out at 58. A much-needed wicket. The two were all set and on course for a big one.
Howout: c Litton Das b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: Good over from Shakib Al Hasan comes to an end. Floated up and on off, Dinesh Chandimal defends it to gully.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Back of the length and outside off, Angelo Mathews blocks it towards silly point.
Shorter and on middle, Angelo Mathews ducks under it.
Back of the length and on leg, Angelo Mathews tries to block it but hits his pads.

Shorter one on middle, Angelo Mathews looks for a pull shot but doesn't get enough power on it. The ball was in the air for some time but just fell short from the fielder on square leg. Lucky for Angelo Mathews.
Fuller and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to block it but misses. The ball just aired past the off pole.
Fuller and on leg, Angelo Mathews looks to defend it but misses as it hits his pads.
Fuller in length and on off, this is eased towards long on for one.
Fuller and outside off, this is left alone.
Floated one on middle, this is eased towards square leg.
Flighted up one middle, this is pushed towards point.
On middle, this is defended towards the off-side.
Goes fuller and outside off, Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.
On a length and on leg, Angelo Mathews flicks it towards square leg and gets a single.
Fuller and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
On a length and on leg, Dinesh Chandimal defends it towards silly point.
On a length and on middle, this is blocked out.
Fuller and outside off, Dinesh Chandimal drives it towards covers for a brace.
Tossed up on middle, this is pushed back towards Shakib Al Hasan.
Outside off, Angelo Mathews punches it towards covers.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended towards mid on.
Sticks to his line and length, this is eased towards mid off.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended towards silly point.
Goes fuller and on off, this is eased back towards the bowler.
Shorter one on middle, Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
Shorter one again, Dinesh Chandimal ducks this one as well.
FOUR! Fuller one this time and outside leg, Dinesh Chandimal drives it through covers for a boundary. That was a delight to watch. Elegant and effortless.
Fuller and on middle, this is blocked out.
Shorter one this time, Dinesh Chandimal ducks under it.
On a length and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
On middle, this is blocked out.
Fuller and on stumps, this is defended out.
On a length and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal uses his feet and blocks it away.
On a length around off, this is defended out.
Goes full, Dinesh Chandimal drives it to covers and straight to the fielder.
A maiden over. On off, blocked out.
Goes fuller and on leg, Angelo Mathews flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
On a length around off, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards square leg for a brace.
Back of the length around the wicket, on off, Dinesh Chandimal guides it towards covers for one.
A length delivery outside off, Angelo Mathews blocks it towards mid off.
Back of the length and on middle, the ball didnt bounce well, Angelo Mathews keeps his eyes on the ball and flicks it towards square leg for one.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
This is floated up full and on the pads, Mathews watchfully keeps it out.
On a length, sliding down leg. Mathews goes onto the back foot and dabs it down towards leg slip for a single.
On middle, Chandimal defends it out.
Slower and shorter on off, Dinesh Chandimal waits for it and punches it off the back foot towards mid off.
That was sharp! Flatter and just quickly coming in on with the angle. Dinesh Chandimal does well to block it out.
Flatter again, around middle and leg. Chandimal nudges it past the man at short leg.
Tad bit short, on off. Angelo Mathews pushes it off the back foot towards extra cover.
On a length and pushed through a bit quicker. Mathews punches it towards covers.
Fuller this time, on off. Mathews drives it back to the bowler.
Almost crept through! Taijul goes quicker and angles it into middle, the ball stays pretty low and skids on. Angelo Mathews just about manages to get his bat down in time.
Tossed up on off and inviting the batter to hit it away. Mathews decides to just push it back towards the bowler.
Fuller in length, around off. Mathews pushes it out on the off side. With the light going down, this might be the final over of the day.
A full ball, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal clips it wide of the mid on fielder and takes a couple of runs. Sri Lanka are up and running on Day 4!
Ebadot serves it on a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and blocks it.
Back of a length, well outside off. Dinesh Chandimal leaves it alone.
This is fuller in length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Good-length ball, just outside off. Dinesh Chandimal prods, opens the bat face and steers it through the backward point region for a boundary.
Short of a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out on the leg side.
Full and on off. Angelo Mathews drives it to the fielder at mid off.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and drives it towards the deep extra cover fielder. The batters cross ends.
On a length, around off. Angelo Mathews defends it.
Floated, on a length, around off. Angelo Mathews blocks it onto the deck.
Fuller in length, outside off. Angelo Mathews drives it to the left of the bowler and collects a run.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal taps it towards point and gets to the other end.

FOUR! Easy pickings! A full ball, around middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it through the mid-wicket region and bags a boundary. Top shot! Bangladesh bowlers have been very inconsistent with their lines and lengths so far!
Good-length ball, just outside off. Dinesh Chandimal prods and pushes it to the cover fielder.
Fuller in length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal lets it be. There is some awkward bounce as the ball goes through to the keeper and Litton Das fails to grab the ball cleanly.
On a length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal shoulders his arms to this one.
A half-volley, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal drives and the fielder at extra cover half-stops it. The batters sneak in a single.
A bit fuller this time from Ebadot, around middle and leg. Angelo Mathews flicks but straight to the mid on fielder.
Tossed up outside off, slightly shorter, Dinesh Chandimal eases it towards point.
On a length and on off, this is defended towards mid off.
Slightly shorter again, on off, this is eased towards point.
On off again, sticks to his length, this is played towards long off for one.
Goes full and straight with a hint of turn, Angelo Mathews tries to block it but just manages to get some bat on it and blocks it.
Outside off, fuller in length, this is punched towards mid off.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed towards covers.
Outside off, fuller in length, this is defended towards silly point.
On a length and on off, Dinesh Chandimal uses his feet and eases it towards mid off. A quick single taken.
Fuller in length and on middle, Angelo Mathews uses his feet and lofts it over long off for a maximum. This was brilliant and effortless.
Fuller on middle, quicker too, this is punched towards long off for one.
Shorter in length and around off, Angelo Mathews ducks under it.
On a length and outside off, slightly shorter, Angelo Mathews jumps a bit and blocks it away.
Back of a length and on middle, Angelo Mathews pulls it and keeps it down, the ball races towards deep square leg and straight to the fielder. A couple of runs taken.
On a length and on leg, Angelo Mathews flicks it towards square leg for one.
Sticks to his length and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it to square leg and rotates the strike.
Goes fuller this time, Angelo Mathews makes room for himself and drives it to the fielder at covers.
Tossed up on middle, this is pushed back towards Taijul Islam.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again, pushed towards the bowler.
On a length and on middle, this is eased towards covers.
On off, this is defended towards short leg.
Sticks to his line and length, Dinesh Chandimal leans a bit and defends it towards silly point.
Fuller one and outside off, this is eased towards mid off. A maiden over from Taijul Islam.
On a length and outside off, Angelo Mathews gets in two minds and tries to block it but gets his bat away at the very last moment. The ball goes into the gloves of the keeper.
On a length and outside off again, Angelo Mathews lets it go.
Change of line, this time outside leg, Angelo Mathews looks to flick it but misses.
On middle, slightly short, Angelo Mathews tries to block it but misses.
Tad fuller and on middle, Angelo Mathews blocks this one out solidly.
Fuller and on leg, this is flicked towards backward square leg. A couple of runs taken.
Flatter and on middle, this is blocked towards short leg.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
On a length and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal uses his feet but hits it straight towards Taijul Islam.
Tossed up outside off, this is defended towards covers.
On off, quicker too, Dinesh Chandimal defends it towards point.
A maiden over. On leg and quicker too, Dinesh Chandimal looks to defend it but misses as it hits his pads.
On off, defended out.
Fuller one on off angling it in, Angelo Mathews blocks this out towards mid off.
Fuller and outside off, Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.
On a length and on middle, Angelo Mathews looks to block it but misses and it hits his pads. A loud appeal but the finger stays down.
Short delivery down the leg side, Angelo Mathews leans back and lets it go.
FOUR! Fullish and outside off, Angelo Mathews looks to flick it but gets an outside edge and the ball races past the third man fence for a boundary.
Fuller and down the leg side, this is defended out.
On off, this is blocked towards silly point.
Fuller and on off, this is eased towards mid off.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off with a hint of turn, Angelo Mathews looks to defend it but gets an inside edge and the ball bounces back.
Flatter and outside off, this is defended towards point for one.
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed back towards Shakib Al Hasan.
Fuller and outside off, this is left out.
Sticks to his line and length, this is defended towards covers for one.
Tossed up and on off, this is blocked towards silly point.
On middle this time, Dinesh Chandimal leans forward and defends it to short leg.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards Shakib Al Hasan.
Flatter and quicker, slightly shorter as well. Angelo Mathews rocks back and slaps it through the cover region for a run.
Chandimal skips down the track and eases this full ball towards long off for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Angelo Mathews defends it with ease.
Floated, on a length, around off. Angelo Mathews prods and keeps it out.
Turn and bounce! Floated, full and outside off. Angelo Mathews looks to drive but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards the point fielder, on the bounce.
Flatter delivery, on a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews taps it towards point.
Tossed up, around off. Dinesh Chandimal defends it off the front foot.

SIX! Excellent use of the feet! Shakib serves it on a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal shimmies down the track and lofts it over long on for a maximum. Not from the middle of the bat but Chandimal won't mind that.
Floated, full and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal drives it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal clears his front leg and drives it wide of the long off fielder for a single.
Around off. Blocked out.
Tosses it up, on a length, on off. Angelo Mathews gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it.
Uppish but safe! Slightly short and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal cuts it aerially just wide of the backward point fielder.
On a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out.
Tossed up, around middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal works it towards mid-wicket.
Good running between the wickets! This is an overpitched ball, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal tucks it towards mid on and gets to the other end.
Too close to cut! This is a quicker ball, coming on with the angle, from off. Angelo Mathews looks to cut but gets cramped for room. It takes the under-edge and lobs onto the deck.
Flighted delivery, on middle. Angelo Mathews blocks it solidly.
Dinesh Chandimal makes use of his feet and pushes this full ball towards the extra cover fielder.
Tossed up, around off. Dinesh Chandimal defends it to the off side.
This is full and just outside off. Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and works it towards cover.
Dinesh Chandimal gets right behind the line of the ball and blocks it with ease.
On a length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal works it wide of the cover fielder and rotates the strike.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Angelo Mathews punches it through the cover region and takes an easy single.
This is a quicker ball, on a length, around off. Angelo Mathews dabs it onto the deck.
Nice and full, around off. Angelo Mathews keeps it out.

FOUR! A full ball, around leg. Dinesh Chandimal kneels and sweeps it through the square leg region for a boundary. Lovely shot!
Floated, on a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews sits back and cuts hard but finds the point fielder.
On a length, on middle. Angelo Mathews blocks it off the front foot.

On a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews pushes it to the extra cover fielder.
Tossed up, on off. Angelo Mathews blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up, around off. Angelo Mathews blocks it with ease.
Mominul Haque starts with a loopy ball, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal lets it be.
This is a flatter ball, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal slaps it through the cover region and takes a single.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Angelo Mathews slaps it through thecover region for a run.

Dinesh Chandimal has been adjudged caught behind and he has opted for a review straightaway. This is a loopy ball, well outside off. Chandimal gets forward and looks to defend. The ball goes past his outside edge and the keeper collects it cleanly. Bangladesh appeal and up goes umpire's finger. Although, the UltraEdge shows no spike as the ball passes the bat and the on-field decision is overturned!
Floated, full and around middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal tucks it to the leg side for a single.
A quicker ball, outside off. Angelo Mathews lets it go through to the keeper.

BEATEN! Turn and bounce for Taijul Islam! This is tossed up, just outside off and spinning away from the batter. Dinesh Chandimal prods to defend but the ball goes past his outside edge. Litton Das behind the sticks, collects the ball and disturbs the stumps in a flash. They appeal for a stumping and the leg umpire sends it upstairs. The replays roll in and it shows that Chandimal had some part of his back foot behind the crease.
Floated, full and on off. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off and just a hint of turn for Taijul Islam. Dinesh Chandimal manages to block it in the end.
Around off, blocked out.
Dinesh Chandimal skips down the track and blocks it out.
This is full and around off. Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and defends it solidly. Another maiden over from Taijul Islam!
Outside off, quicker, left alone.
Flatter and on off, Mathews pushes it to covers.
Fuller and on off, Mathews drives but finds cover.
Shorter in length and outside off, Mathews slaps it through covers and takes one.
Fuller and on off, Chandimal strokes it to covers.
Good stop, saves a run! Shorter and on off, this is pushed to the left of the fielder at cover who dives and does well to not let the batters take one.
A little too short again, Mathews slaps it through covers and gets to the other end.
On off, this is pushed down to long off for one.
Fires it on middle, Mathews defends it out.
On the shorter side, Mathews stays back and pushes it to covers.
On middle, blocked.
Fires this one on the off pole. Mathews hangs back and plays it to covers. Just the two from the over then.
A little too short, Chandimal pushes it down to long off and gets to the other end.
Shorter and outside off, Mathews slaps it through covers for one.

Tosses it above the eye line and lands it on off, Mathews pushes it to cover.
