On middle, Chandimal flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle, defended yet again.
On the stumps, this one skids through. Chandimal blocks.
A maiden then by Taijul! On off, Chandimal plays it out on the off side.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Bangs this one short and on the body, gets big on Chandimal. He fends it away by taking a hand off the handle.
Back of a length and on off, Chandimal pushes it to covers.
On middle, this one stays a touch low. Chandimal gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
Angled into the pads, Chandimal works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Good length and on off, Mathews defends it out.
Fuller and on off, Chandimal strokes it to covers.
Gives it air and lands it on off, Chandimal defends it on the off side.
Angled into the pads, Chandimal works it through square leg for one. 350 comes up for Sri Lanka.
Angled into the pads, this is nudged around the corner for one.
On middle, quicker, kept out.
On the stumps, Chandimal keeps it out.
Back of a length and on middle, Mathews defends it on the leg side.
On middle, Mathews works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter and on off, Mathews pushes it off the back foot to mid off.
Back of a length and on off, Mathews pushes it to covers.
Down the leg side, Mathews looks to flick but misses.
Shorter and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Leading edge but safe! On middle, this one holds its line. Dinesh Chandimal looks to work it on the leg side which is against the turn. It goes off a soft leading edge back towards the bowler.
On middle, defended.
On the stumps, blocked.
Flatter and on the stumps, blocked out.
FIFTY FOR CHANDIMAL! On off, this is eased down to long off for one. This has been a good knock from him so far but he would be aware that he still has a long way to go in this innings.
On the stumps, defended.
That is a nasty delivery! This is on a length and around off, it lands and then takes off. Chandimal hops and tries to fend it away by taking his eyes off the ball. It hits his glove.
Back of a length and on off, Dinesh Chandimal pushes it through covers for one.
Angled into middle, Mathews works it to mid-wicket.
On off, Mathews pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! The trail is now just the 8 runs! Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On off, defended.
Tossed up, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out.
FOUR! Excellent use of the feet yet again! Tossed up, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal skips down the track and flicks it through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
On a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal blocks it with ease.
Around off, blocked out.
Tosses it up, around off. Dinesh Chandimal dabs it onto the deck.
Floated, full and around off. Dinesh Chandimal defends it watchfully.
Back of a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews leaves it alone.

A short ball, around leg. Angelo Mathews looks to tuck it to the leg side. He misses and gets hit just above his thigh pad. The ball evades the diving keeper to his left and the batters collect a leg bye.
Slightly short and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal punches it to the extra cover fielder.
On a good length and around off. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal nudges it to the leg side and takes a single.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Angelo Mathews stays back and works it towards mid-wicket.
Full and around off. Dinesh Chandimal drives it down to long off and rotates the strike.
Taijul Islam comes 'round the wicket and serves a loopy ball, around leg. Angelo Mathews prods and pads it away.
This is flatter and around middle. Angelo Mathews rocks back and eases it to long off for a run. The scores are level now.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out, off the front foot.
This is sprayed down the leg side. Dinesh Chandimal tickles it through fine leg for a brace. Sri Lanka lead by 2 runs!
Dinesh Chandimal skips down the track and drives it down to long off for one run.
Shakib starts his spell with a full ball, around leg. Dinesh Chandimal works it behind square on the leg side for one run.
Nicely tossed up, on middle. Angelo Mathews blocks it with ease.
Floated, full and around off. Angelo Mathews gets forward and defends it.
A bit quicker this time, on a length, around off. Angelo Mathews hangs back and dabs it onto the deck.
Slower through the air, full and around off. Angelo Mathews gets solid in his front foot defence.
This is an overpitched ball, around off. Angelo Mathews digs it out watchfully. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Taijul starts with a flatter ball, around leg. Dinesh Chandimal nudges it around the corner and takes a single.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Angelo Mathews rocks back and punches it towards long off for a single.
A bit quicker, on a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out with soft hands.
Quicker through the air, full and on off. Dinesh Chandimal prods and defends it.
Tosses it up, around off. Dinesh Chandimal blocks it with ease.
This is a bit quicker, full and around off. Dinesh Chandimal gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Ahmed starts with a full ball, angling in from middle. Angelo Mathews flicks it towards the mid on fielder.
Ahmed drags his length back, around middle. Angelo Mathews blocks it out.
Good-length ball, around middle. Angelo Mathews keeps it out.
This is full and outside off. Angelo Mathews prods and drives it to the extra cover fielder.
Back of a length, around off. Angelo Mathews taps it to the off side.

Angelo Mathews has been adjudged caught behind and he has reviewed the decision straightaway! This is a length ball, just outside off and shaping away late. Mathews feels for it and has a tentative poke at it. The ball whizzes past the outside edge and goes through to the keeper. Bangladesh appeal and the umpire raises his finger after taking a lot of time. However, the UltraEdge shows a flat line as the ball passes the bat and the on-field decision has been overturned yet again.
Tossed up, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal drives it wide of the extra cover fielder and collects a couple of runs.
Chandimal skips down the track and works it to long off for a single.
This is flatter and quicker, outside off. Angelo Mathews taps it to the off side and gets to the other end.
Full and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal drives it hard towards the long off region and takes a run.
Floated, full and around off. Mathews keeps it out.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Angelo Mathews smothers the spin well and dabs it onto the deck.
On a length, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal nudges it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
A yorker-length ball, on middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, around the corridor of uncertainty. Angelo Mathews throws his bat at it but the ball goes past his blade.
This is much fuller, around off. Angelo Mathews pushes it to the fielder at mid on.
Good-length ball, around off and moving away just that little bit. Angelo Mathews looks to block with soft hands but it goes off the thick outside towards the gully fielder.
On a length, around middle. Angelo Mathews tucks it to the leg side.
A loopy ball, full and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal slaps it through the extra cover region for just the single.
Slower through the air, on a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews stays back and cuts it to the point fielder.
This is darted on the pads. Angelo Mathews tucks it behind square on the leg side and collects a single.
Dinesh Chandimal skips down the track so Shakib Al Hasan serves it wider outside off. Chandimal keeps it out in the end.
Full and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal drives it through the cover region and rotates the strike.
Tossed up, around middle. Angelo Mathews blocks it out.
Short of a length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal slaps it through the cover region for a brace.
FOUR! Short and wide and Dinesh Chandimal pounces on it! Back of a length, well outside off. Chandimal sits back and cuts it through the point region. The ball races away to the fence.

An appeal for LBW but turned down! Bangladesh have opted for a review though! This is a length ball, jagging back in late from middle. Dinesh Chandimal looks to flick it but he misses and gets hit low on his pad. The UltraEdge shows that there was no bat involved. The Ball Tracker shows that the ball would have missed the leg stump by some margin. Bangladesh lose their review.
On a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal dabs it onto the deck.
A full ball, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it aerially through square leg and gets to the other end.
Back of a length, outside off. Mathews hangs back and slaps it through covers for one run. He moves to 97!
Flatter and on the stumps. Mathews tucks it to the leg side.

Fuller, on middle and leg. Mathews flicks it to square leg and scampers across for a quick single. The fielder scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end but Angelo Mathews had his blade grounded and inside the crease. They take one.
This is floated, full and around middle. Dinesh Chandimal clips it towards mid-wicket.
Full and on middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal nudges it around the corner and takes a single.
Flatter ball, around off. Angelo Mathews gets forward and blocks it.
A quicker ball, on a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews hangs back and punches it to the fielder at extra cover.
Floated, full and on off. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out.
Dinesh Chandimal skips down the track and pushes it towards the cover fielder.
Flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal lets it be.
Another quicker ball, on a length, and well outside off. Dinesh Chandimal shoulders his arms to this one.
A bit slower through the air, around off. Dinesh Chandimal defends it to the off side.
Floated, on a length, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal looks to work it on the leg side but he gets a leading edge which goes to the right of the bowler.
Slightly short and outside off. Angelo Mathews slaps it through the off side and collects a run. He moves to 99!
Flatter ball, outside off and turning in late. Dinesh Chandimal manages to keep it out in the end as the ball stayed a touch low.
This is darted on the pads. Chandimal just helps it on its way through fine leg for one run.
On a length, around off and spinning in sharply. Angelo Mathews rocks back and works it towards square leg.
This is a quicker ball, on a length, on middle. Angelo Mathews sits back and punches it towards mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, around off and turning in late. Angelo Mathews prods and works it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
A loopy ball, well outside off. Dinesh Chandimal does not bother playing at that one.
FOUR! Cut away! A short ball, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal rocks back and cuts it past the fielder at backward point for a boundary. Excellent use of the crease from Chandimal.
Around off, blocked out.
Tosses it up, on off. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out.
On a length, around leg. Dinesh Chandimal prods and helps it through the fine leg region for a single.
Slightly short and outside off. Angelo Mathews cuts hard but straight to the point fielder who dives low to his right to stop the ball.
Tossed up, around off. Dinesh Chandimal blocks it.
Chandimal skips down the track and nudges it to the leg side.
Floated, full and on middle. Dinesh Chandimal eases it down to long on for one run.

HUNDRED FOR MATHEWS! Back-to-back centuries from Angelo Mathews and this has been a gritty knock from the experienced campaigner! His 13th Test hundred and second against Bangladesh. This was a flatter ball, on middle. Mathews nudges it to the leg side and scampers through to the other end.
On a length, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal works it through mid-wicket and rotates the strike. 400 comes up for Sri Lanka!
Tosses it up, around off. Angelo Mathews keeps it out.
A loopy ball, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal advances down the track and drives it to the mid on fielder.
Floated, full and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal drives it through the long off region and hands the strike back to Mathews.
FOUR! SMASHED! This is dragged down, around middle. Angelo Mathews rocks back and pulls it over the mid-wicket fielder to bag a boundary.
On a length, around off. Mathews punches it towards the fielder at extra cover.
Full and around middle. Angelo Mathews tucks it to the leg side.
This is full and well outside off. Angelo Mathews drives hard but finds the cover fielder.
A full ball, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it through the square leg region for a brace.
Short of a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal dabs it onto the deck.
Back of a length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal sits back and punches it through the cover region for a couple of runs. He moves to 90 now!
Short ball, outside off. Chandimal cuts it to point for a single.
A length ball, drifting down the leg side. Mathews tries to flick it away but misses.
Full length, on off. Mathews gets it to square leg off the inside edge. The batters cross for a single.
Darted on the pads, Mathews clips it to the leg side.

NOT OUT! There is a loud appeal for lbw and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. It is tossed up, full and around off, turns in a bit. Mathews gets on the front foot and tries to sweep it away but misses. The ball goes through to hit him on the pads. Hossain appeals and the umpire agrees. Although, Mathews wastes no time in taking the review. The UltraEdge confirms that there is spike as the ball passes the blade. Mosaddek Hossain is yet to grab is maiden Test wicket.
Flatter ball, around off. Angelo Mathews hangs back and punches it to the cover fielder.
A quicker ball, on a length, around middle. Angelo Mathews sits back and nudges it towards mid-wicket.
On a length, around middle. Angelo Mathews keeps it out.
Slightly short and outside off. Angelo Mathews pushes it to the fielder at cover, off the back foot.

FOUR! Ebadot Hossain starts his spell with a loosener, a full ball, well outside off. Dinesh Chandimal prods and carves it through the cover region for a cracking boundary. A 'HIT ME' ball from Ebadot.

FOUR! Nicely worked! Back of a length, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal stays back and just steers it through the vacant third man region for another boundary. That shot also brings up the 150-run stand between these two!
A low full toss, around off. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it back to the bowler.

HUNDRED FOR CHANDIMAL! A full ball, outside off. Chandimal pushes it towards mid off and gets to the other end. A beautifully compiled century from Dinesh Chandimal and he takes all the applause from his teammates, by raising the bat towards the change room. 12th Test hundred for Chandimal!
An overpitched ball, around off. Angelo Mathews digs it out watchfully.
A short ball, around off. Angelo Mathews ducks under it.
Tossed up, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Floated, full and around middle. Angelo Mathews works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, turning in from outside off. Angelo Mathews nudges it to the leg side.
A very full ball, on middle. Angelo Mathews squeezes it out towards mid on by skipping down the track.
Aerial but safe! Tossed up, on middle. Angelo Mathews prods and flicks it uppishly towards the mid-wicket fielder.
On a length, around middle. Angelo Mathews blocks it with ease.
This is full and around middle. Dinesh Chandimal eases it down the ground towards long on for a single.
Taijul Islam goes over the wicket and serves it down the leg side. Angelo Mathews lets it be.
Floated, full and on middle. Angelo Mathews pushes it through covers for one run.
Full and on middle. Dinesh Chandimal nudges it to the leg side for a single.
A loopy ball, full and on leg. Angelo Mathews looks to flick but he misses as the ball turns past his blade. He gets hit high on his pad. Although the ball was pitched way outside leg.
On a length, around off. Angelo Mathews keeps it out.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off and turning in late. Dinesh Chandimal nudges it to the leg side.
Chandimal shimmies down the track and works it to long on for a run.
This is on a length, around middle. Angelo Mathews tucks it towards mid-wicket for one run.
An overpitched ball, on off. Dinesh Chandimal digs it out back to the bowler.
Full and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal drives it to the cover fielder.
Slower through the air, full and outside off. Dinesh Chandimal keeps it out.
Tossed up, down leg. Angelo Mathews brings out the reverse-sweep and works it towards point for a single.
This is sprayed down leg. Dinesh Chandimal helps it towards the short fine leg fielder.
On a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal taps it to the off side and gets to the other end.
A full ball, down leg. Angelo Mathews sweeps it towards the short fine leg fielder.
Floated, full and around off. Angelo Mathews pushes it through the off side and collects an easy single.
Full and on middle. Dinesh Chandimal skips down the track and works it to long on for a run.
Full, on middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal eases it to long on for a single.
Flatter and on off. Mathews hits it to long on for a single.
Darted on the pads, Chandimal clips it to square leg.
LEG BYE! Flighted and full, angled down leg. Chandimal looks to sweep it away but misses. The ball goes to square leg off his pads. They collect a leg bye.
On off, worked towards mid on.
Flatter, on the pads. Angelo Mathews tucks it to the leg side.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal prods and taps it towards cover.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Tosses it up, around off. Dinesh Chandimal skips down the track and whacks it back past the bowler for a boundary.
On a length, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal eases it towards long on for one run.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Angelo Mathews blocks it.
Tossed up, around off. Angelo Mathews dabs it onto the deck.
A quicker ball, full and outside off. Angelo Mathews drives it straight back to the bowler.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Dinesh Chandimal punches it back to the bowler.
Dinesh Chandimal skips down the track, so Mosaddek Hossain serves a quicker ball. Chandimal yorks himself but manages to keep it out.
This is eased down the ground by Dinesh Chandimal for a single.
A quicker ball, around middle. Angelo Mathews dabs it back to the bowler.
An overpitched ball, around off. Angelo Mathews heaves it without much timing towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
A full ball, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal works it to long on for one run.
Floated, full and around off. Dinesh Chandimal gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it to the off side.
Sharp turn! On a length, around off and spinning away late. Dinesh Chandimal adjusts well in the end and guides it past the short third man fielder for a couple of runs.
Full and around middle. Dinesh Chandimal runs down the track and drives it past the bowler for a single.
This is full and on middle. Angelo Mathews plays the reverse-sweep. There is a fielder stationed in the deep so the batters manage only a run.
Flatter ball, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal cuts it to deep cover for one run.
This is darted on the pads. Angelo Mathews nudges it around the corner and rotates the strike.
An overpitched ball, on middle. Angelo Mathews manages to somehow dig it out.
FOUR! Tossed up, on middle. Angelo Mathews kneels and slog-sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary. Both the batters have certainly changed gears now!
Slightly short and around middle. Angelo Mathews nudges it through square leg and takes a single.
Floated, full and just outside off. Dinesh Chandimal prods and flicks it to the mid-wicket fielder.
Another overpitched delivery, on middle. Dinesh Chandimal whips it through the mid-wicket region for a run.
On a length, around off. Angelo Mathews dabs it onto the deck.
Good-length ball, around off. Dinesh Chandimal blocks it off the front foot.
A length ball, around middle. Dinesh Chandimal gets forward and tucks it towards mid-wicket.
A slower ball, into the wicket, outside off. Dinesh Chandimal miscues his pull shot towards deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Slapped away with disdain! Back of a length, outside off. Angelo Mathews flat-bats it back past the bowler and bags a boundary.
A short ball, around off. Angelo Mathews tucks it towards deep mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Short of a length, around off. Dinesh Chandimal defends it out watchfully. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Angled into the pads, Mathews works it to mid-wicket. He wants one but is sent back.
Flatter and on middle, defended towards cover for one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to short fine leg.
On off, defended.
On the stumps, kept out by coming on the front foot.
Short and down the leg side, Mathews really looks to pull it hard but misses.
Bangs it short and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one.
Short again and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal looks to play the upper cut but is beaten.
FOUR! Pulled away hard! Short and on middle, this is hammered through mid-wicket for a boundary.
SHort and outside off, left alone.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a sharp, sharp catch and finally, Bangladesh have managed to break the 6th wicket stand. Brilliant innings from Chandimal comes to an end. His intentions were clear  though, he had come out all guns blazing. Chandimal had smacked this one. It was full and outside off, he powered it towards cover but uppishly. Tamim dives to his left and takes a sharp catch.
Howout: c Tamim Iqbal b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: On off, this is pushed to covers.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
The sweep comes out, not off the middle, it goes more off the inner half through square leg for one.
On off, blocked.
EDGY RUNS! Dickwella steps out, he then looks to work it on the leg side but this one does not turn. It goes off the outside edge past first slip for two more.
Well played in the end! Shorter and on middle, it is the quicker one. Defended.

NOT OUT! Nothing on Ultra Edge and there is a big gap between bat and ball too! A short one down the leg side. Mathews looks to pull but misses. Ebadot Hossain is celebrating after the keeper takes it. Mathews holds his ground. Ebadot Hossain then turns and appeals but turned down. Ebadot Hossain wants it to be reviewed and it is. Replays show that the on-field call is the right one.
FOUR! This time the short ball is hammered! It is on the body, Mathews pulls it hard and through square leg for a boundary.
Another short one, this is hit through square leg for one more.
Good stop! Shorter and outside off, Dickwella guides it towards point. The fielder dives to his right and makes a good stop.
Angled into the pads, this is tucked around the corner for one.
Bangs it short again and on the body, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.
FOUR! That is a strong sweep shot! On middle, Dickwella hammers it over the square leg for a boundary.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Very well bowled! Slows it up and lands it around off, this lands and spins away. Mathews pushes at it, it goes more off the outside edge towards short third man for noe.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ultra Edge shows a spike and Dickwella has to walk back! That may have surprised a few. Pretty sure not many, actually nobody appealed for a caught behind! Bangladesh though won't mind how the wickets come! Dickwella dances down the wicket, this is fired outside off. Dickwella throws his bat at it but seems to have missed it. Das whips the bails off and appeals but not with a lot of excitment. It is an appeal for a stumping. The umpire takes it upstairs. However, they check first if there is an edge and Ultra Edge shows a spike as the ball passes the bat. Good passage of play this for the host.
Howout: c Litton Das b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: Tossed up on middle, defended.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
FOUR! Nice and fine! Angled into the pads, Mathews tickles it fine on the leg side and this one races away to the fence.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and outside off, Mathews looks to drive but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket for one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Timed wonderfully! Shorter and outside off, Mathews waits and then plays it past point for a boundary. He moves into the 140s.
On off, defended.
Tosses it up on off, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Fired on the pads, Mathews looks to sweep but it goes off the glove on the leg side.
A single now as this is pushed down to long off.
On middle, defended.
Attacks the stumps again, kept out nicely.
FOUR! That is a poor delivery! A half volley outside off, Mendis leans into it and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, length ball, Mendis slashes at it but misses.
Effort ball, short and outside off. Mendis looks to pull but misses. The keeper leaps and takes it above his head.
FOUR! Flayed away and runs are flowing now. 500 up for Lanka! Outside off, Mendis goes after it and it flies through point for a boundary.

OUT! THREE REDS! Not sure why the review was taken! That always looked out. Mendis had almost walked off but right at the end, signaled the 'T'. To no avail though and he takes a review along with him too! On middle, Ebadot Hossain bowls a lot straighter this time after bowling quite a few outside off. Mendis shuffles across and looks to flick but misses to get hit in front. An appeal and the finger is raised. Mendis starts walking off but in the end, decides to review. Replays show that the on-field call is the right one. Bangladesh into the tail now. Can they now make quick work of the remaining wickets?
Howout: lbw b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: BEATEN! That is a beauty! Goes wide of the crease, angles it into the off pole, this lands and moves away. Praveen Jayawickrama is beaten as he tries to block.
Shorter and outside off, Mathews guides it past point for one.
On middle, defended.

OUT! TAKEN! Shakib has his 5th! 19 Test fifer! That is a beauty of a delivery. Way too good for a number 10 batter. This is tossed up on off, it lands and spins away sharply. Praveen Jayawickrama looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge and into the hands of Das. He takes it on the second attempt. An appeal, the umpire gives it a thought and then raises the finger. Praveen Jayawickrama won't be too disappointed after looking at how that spun.
Howout: c Litton Das b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: The Lankan spinners will be licking their lips after watching the last two balls. This one lands on off and then spins away. Fernando is beaten as he tries to put bat on ball.
A little too full and on middle, kept out.
On off, the arm ball. Blocked nicely.
Fires it on the stumps, Angelo Mathews eases it towards mid-wicket.
On a length and outside off, Angelo Mathews punches it towards covers for one.
On a good length and on middle, this is flicked towards mid-wicket.
Goes for a shorter one and on leg, Asitha Fernando ducks under it.
This is much better from Ebadot Hossain. Fuller and outside off, Asitha Fernando looks to loft it but misses. A loud appeal but the replay shows that it was the bat that hit the ground.
On a length and on middle, Asitha Fernando lofts it over covers for a brace.

OUT! RUN OUT! Tossed up on middle, this is lofted towards long off. Angelo Mathews calls for a second run. Rahim was quick with the ball and throws it towards Shakib Al Hasan who hits the stumps. The decision goes upstairs and the replay shows that Asitha Fernando was too short of his crease. Sri Lanka have been bowled out for 506.
Howout: run out (Mushfiqur Rahim / Shakib Al Hasan)

Commentary: A length ball outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone.
Similar to the last delivery, this is left towards the keeper as well.
Fuller one this time and on the stumps, Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it out.
Touch fuller, outside off and swinging it away, Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to drive it but misses.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
A maiden over. Fuller and wide outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets on his knees and looks to drive this as well but misses.
Fuller and around off, Tamim Iqbal blocks it away.
Fullish and on leg, Tamim Iqbal looks to flick it but just gets a hint on his pads and races towards the keeper who just manages to get his glove on it. A single taken.
On middle, this is blocked out.
On a len and down the leg, Mahmudul Hasan Joy tries to flick it but misses as it hits his pads. A loud appeal but the finger stays down.
FOUR! A lucky one for Mahmudul Hasan Joy. On a length and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy tries to block it but gets a thick outside edge as it races past the fence towards the third man.
FOUR! On a length and on off, this time Mahmudul Hasan Joy waits for the ball and guides it towards the backward point using the pace of the ball. The ball goes over the ropes for a boundary.
Comes around the wicket bowling it fuller and on middle, Tamim Iqbal blocks it out solidly.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
A low full toss outside off, Tamim Iqbal tries to drive it but misses.
Fuller and outside off this time, Tamim Iqbal defends it towards covers.
Fuller and on leg, this is defended towards the mid on region.
Sticks to his length and outside leg, Tamim Iqbal looks to flick it but misses.
Touch fuller and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it out solidly.
On a length and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it towards silly point.
Fuller and on the stumps this time, Mahmudul Hasan Joy eases it towards mid on.
Too short and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks under it. This was well over Mahmudul Hasan Joy. Wide called.
On a length and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it towards mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Fuller and outside leg, quicker too, this is eased towards mid on.
On a good length and on off, this is pushed back towards Asitha Fernando.
DROPPED! Outside off and fuller, Mahmudul Hasan Joy tries to block but gets an outside and the ball goes straight towards the slip fielder who drops it. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets a lucky escape.
Fuller and on middle, this is blocked out.

Fuller and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy tries to block it but he misses and the ball hits his pad. A loud appeal from Kasun Rajitha but the finger stays down. Replay shows that it had a slight inside edge before it hit the pads.
On middle, this is eased towards mid on.
On a length and outside leg, Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to flick it but misses.
FOUR! Fuller and on leg, Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it towards square leg as the ball races past the fence for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Back of a length and outside off, Tamim Iqbal tries to block it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes towards the second slip fielder where and Kusal Mendis couldn't catch it for the first time. He juggles with the ball a couple of times but manages to hold on to it in the end. Sri Lanka finally get a breakthrough. Tamim Iqbal goes for a pair.
Howout: c Kusal Mendis b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: On a length and on off, this is guided towards covers.
Fuller and outside leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto lets it go.
Fullish and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto leaves it alone.
Sticks to his length bowling it wide outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto shoulders arms and leaves it towards the keeper.
A wicket-maiden from Asitha Fernando. Fuller in length and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it towards covers.
Fuller and on leg, Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it towards square leg for one.
On a length and on middle, Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it towards short leg.
Fuller and on middle, Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a quick single.
Fuller in length and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy eases it towards mid on for one.
On a length and on leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it towards square leg.
Fuller and outside off, this is driven towards covers and in the gap. He wanted a couple but Mahmudul Hasan Joy sends him back.
On a good length and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it away towards silly point.

OUT! RUN OUT! Touch fuller in length and on middle, Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it towards mid off. He goes for a quick single. There was a bit of a mix-up between the two and the fielder, Praveen Jayawickrama takes a direct hit which hits the stumps. The decision goes upstairs and the replay shows that he was short of his crease.
Howout: run out (Praveen Jayawickrama)

Commentary: On off, blocked out.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended as well.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
A wicket-maiden for Asitha Fernando. On a length and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy jumps a bit and blocks it out towards silly point.
A length ball outside off angling it inside, Mominul Haque blocks it out.

Sri Lanka have opted for a review for caught behind! This is a fuller one, outside off, Mominul Haque looks to drive it but misses. The ball goes towards the keeper and a loud shout from Sri Lanka. The finger stays down and they go for a review. Ultra edge shows that there was a fine spike and Mominul Haque has to walk back to the pavilion. Bangladesh lose their third wicket in just eight overs and they need a good partnership now. Pressure on Bangladesh now!
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Kasun Rajitha

Commentary: A full ball on the pads. Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it behind square on the leg side for a brace. The centurion from the first innings gets off the mark straightaway.
On a length, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim keeps it out.
Rajitha pitches it full, around middle and leg. Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it through the mid-wicket region and collects a couple of runs.
On a length and angling in from middle. Mushfiqur Rahim dabs it onto the deck.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust and Bangladesh are in deep, deep trouble now. This is a good-length ball, around the corridor of uncertainty. Mahmudul Hasan Joy has a poke at it. There is also some extra bounce for the bowler. The ball takes Joy's outside edge and goes straight to Kusal Mendis at second slip. He takes it without juggling it this time. Sri Lanka are all over Bangladesh at the moment.
Howout: c Kusal Mendis b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Litton Das blocks it out.
This is a length ball, nipping back in from just outside off. Das sits back and defends it with ease.
Short of a length, around off. Litton Das hangs back and gets right behind the line of the ball to block this one.
A full ball, well outside off. Litton Das looks for a booming drive but it goes off the thick inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
Asitha Fernando bangs it into the deck, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim ducks under it. End to another successful over for Sri Lanka.
A length ball, outside off. Litton Das leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, well outside off. Litton Das does not bother playing at that one.
Back of a length, around middle. Litton Das defends it solidly this time.
Full and outside off. Litton Das leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Litton Das sits back and dabs it onto the deck.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Litton Das drives but finds the extra cover fielder.
Back of a length and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim defends it out towards short leg.
On a length and on middle, Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it back towards Asitha Fernando.
Back of a length and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim defends this one as well.
Shorter one this time, Mushfiqur Rahim ducks under it.
Change of length and outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim lets it go towards the keeper.
Fuller this time and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks this one towards the on side for one.
FOUR! Flatter and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim pulls it through backward square leg for a boundary. That was a gift from Praveen Jayawickrama.
On a good length and on middle, this is pushed back towards Praveen Jayawickrama.
Fuller and outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim leans forward and blocks it away.
FOUR! On a length and on middle, Mushfiqur Rahim makes room for himself and pulls it towards backward square leg for a boundary.
Fuller and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it towards square leg for one.
Flatter and on middle, this is defended out solidly and back towards the bowler. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4.
A very full delivery, around middle and leg. Mushfiqur Rahim pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller delivery, outside off, at 135 clicks. Mushfiqur Rahim leans forward and defends it towards cover.
Swinging in, fuller ball, around middle. Mushfiqur Rahim pushes it towards the fielder at mid on.
On a length now, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it alone.
Fuller length ball, angling in around middle. Mushfiqur Rahim presents the full face of the bat and blocks it out solidly.
Another inswinger, around off, on a fuller length, at 136.4 clicks. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it out towards cover. A maiden to begin with!
Kasun Rajitha begins with a fuller ball, shaping away, around off. Litton Das leans and taps it towards point.
Another fuller ball, outside off. Litton Das pushes it through cover for a brace. Bangladesh are underway on Day 5!
On a length, outside off. Litton Das pushes it towards point.
Another good drive! Fuller ball, outside off. Litton Das presses forward and drives it gently past cover. Another couple of runs taken!
Well bowled! On a length, this one nips back in, around middle and leg. Litton Das gets rapped on his pads as he tries to block this one. An appeal for LBW, but not given. That was probably too high.

FOUR! First boundary of the morning! A length ball, jagging back in around middle. Litton Das gets his bat down late as he tries to block it. The ball goes off his outside edge over the slip fielder for a boundary.
On a length, around middle. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it out.
Another good-length delivery, around middle and off. Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it out solidly.
Back of a length, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim shows the full face of his bat and defends it from within his crease.
Length delivery, outside off, angling in. Mushfiqur Rahim offers no shot on that.
Swinging in around middle, fuller ball. Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it off the front foot.
Shorter ball, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim gets on his toes and blocks it out. Another maiden over from Asitha Fernando.
No ball! Outside off, touch shorter. Litton Das taps it towards point off the back foot.
Fuller ball, around middle and leg. Litton Das defends it out towards the leg side.
Outside off, on a length. Litton Das blocks it out.
On a length, shaping away. Litton Das leaves it alone.
Another length delivery, outside off. Litton Das lets that go through.
On a length, outside off. Litton Das pushes it towards point.
Wide of off, fuller ball. Litton Das pushes it towards gully.

NO BALL AND FOUR! Shorter ball, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim stands tall, and punches it off the back foot past gully for a boundary. Lovely shot from Mushfiqur Rahim! Asitha Fernando has overstepped here and a no ball is called!
On a length, around middle. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it out.
Another good-length delivery, around middle and off. Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it out.
Much fuller now, angling in around off. Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it towards the off side.
FOUR! Edgy runs! Mushfiqur Rahim played that intentionally though. A length ball, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim brings his bat down late as the ball goes off his outside edge past gully for a boundary.
Outside off, on a length. Mushfiqur Rahim shoulders his arms at it.
Another length delivery, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it alone.
Beaten! Well bowled! A length delivery, shaping away outside off. Litton Das stays in his crease and tries to block this but he gets beaten on the outside edge. Lovely delivery!
Much fuller now, angling in around middle. Litton Das pushes it towards mid on.
On a length, shaping away, outside off, at 130.2 clicks. This one stays low as well. Litton Das leaves it alone.
Fuller ball, swinging away, around middle and off. Litton Das pushes it towards cover.
Another beauty! A length ball, nipping back in around the fourth stump line. Litton Das looks to block this but he bails out in the end.

A length delivery, angling down leg. Litton Das looks to flick this but he misses. The ball goes behind to the keeper who dives to his left and collects the ball. A huge shout for caught behind and the umpire raises his finger. Litton Das opts for a review immediately. The replay shows that the ball brushes off his pads. No bat involved there! The on-field decision needs to be overturned!
Fuller ball, tosses it up, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim drives it firmly towards deep cover for a single.
Loopy delivery, very full, around middle. Litton Das pushes it towards mid off. No run taken!
Tosses it up, full, on middle. Litton Das defends it out.
Another fuller ball, around middle and leg. Litton Das presses forward and blocks it out.
Flighted delivery, fuller ball, outside off, spinning away a tad. Litton Das leaves it alone.
Another loopy ball, outside off, fuller ball. Litton Das leans forward and lets that go through to the keeper.
Rajitha goes full and wide, Rahim shoulders arms to it.
On a nagging length, on the fifth stump line and shaping away nicely. Just a bit too wide to force a shot out of the batter.

OUT! Cleaned up! Cracker of a delivery from Kasun Rajitha and he gets the big fish. This is slanted in off a length, close to the off pole. The ball just nips back in sharply and there's that uneven bounce again. The ball keeps low and before Mushfiqur Rahim can get his bat down, the ball skids through and rattles the off stump. Huge, huge moment in the Test match and in the series as well. Rajitha is all pumped up and understandably so.
Howout: b Kasun Rajitha

Commentary: Ooh, Shakib Al Hasan just about got some bat on that one. Kasun Rajitha switches to around the wicket and angles it in a long way from outside off. Shakib falls over a bit as he gets an inside edge onto the bat. Rajitha has a stifled appeal but that's all it is.
Fuller and on off, kept out by Shakib.
This is very full and angling into middle, Shakib Al Hasan punches it back towards the bowler. Successful over for Kasun Rajitha, a wicket maiden.
Gives it a nice loop and drifts it onto middle. Das defends it off the front foot.
Nicely flighted, around off. Das blocks it out.
This is tossed up, around off. Litton Das drives it straight to the man at extra cover.

Unlucky! Praveen Jayawickrama floats it up around off, he gets it to drift and then gets the turn and bounce as well. Litton Das is suckered into the drive and the outside edge is induced. The ball goes past first slip and Das picks up a couple of runs.
Looped up, fuller and around off. Sharp turn and bounce on offer for Jayawickrama but Das makes a watchful leave.
Too full and too straight, this is turned through mid-wicket for a single.
Peach! Rajitha pitches it up on a length, in that channel around off and the ball just nips away sharply off the surface. Litton Das has a tentative push at it but gets beaten past the outside edge.

Now then, was there a faint edge there? This is a bit wider, outside off. Das looks to play away from the body and misses. There is a slight noise as the ball goes past the bat but Sri Lanka decide against the review. Replay shows that there was no bat involved.
Rajitha looks to swing it into the pads but spills it down the leg side.
Nicely bowled! On a length, around off and shaping away. Play and a miss from Das.

FIVE WIDES! Well, that one seems to have slipped off. Rajitha looks to attack the pads but ends up serving it way, way down leg. No chance for the keeper and the ball runs away into the fine leg fence.
Fuller and outside off, left alone by Litton Das.

Length again, close to the off pole. Litton Das has no idea if it's going to shape away or nip back in and has a poke at it. The ball comes off the splice of the bat and goes towards mid-wicket. A quick single is taken.
On a length, drifted onto the pads. Litton Das goes back in his crease to push it out on the leg side for a single.
A bit of a yes and no but they make it in the end. On off, Shakib Al Hasan presses forward and pushes it towards covers for a quick single.
Litton Das just seems a bit edgy out there at the moment. Floated up, on a shorter length. Das looks to come forward but goes back at the last moment, does well to fend off the extra bounce.
On off, Das blocks it out.
Around middle, Das makes another watchful block.
On the pads, Das goes on the back foot and tucks it pst short leg for a single.
Full and straight, Das nudges it to short mid-wicket.
Just too full and too straight, flicked away to fine leg for an easy single.
FOUR! Thumped! A half-volley, around off. Shakib Al Hasan stays on the front foot and punches it sweetly through extra cover for a glorious boundary. That will give him a lot of confidence.
Rajitha pulls back the length a touch and angles it into middle. Shakib defends it out.
FOUR! Just a bit short and there's some width on offer. Shakib Al Hasan hammers it through the cover region for a second boundary in the over. Kasun Rajitha looks like he needs a break.
FOUR! Poor bowling and Shakib Al Hasan has made full use of it. Full and wide, driven hard and through covers for back-to-back boundaries.
Drifted onto middle, Das defends it off the front foot.
Floated up, around middle. Litton Das keeps it out.
Very full and on middle, Das gets an inside edge onto the pads. Jayawickrama seems a bit excited but no one supports him. The replay shows that the ball might have hit bat and pad at the same time.
On off, kept out.
Nicely flighted, around off. Litton Das strides forward to defend.
Flatter delivery, on off. Litton Das rocks back and edges it past first slip to pick up a single.
Right on the money, top of the off line. Litton Das hangs back to keep it out.
Keeping real low! A bit fuller and wider, Das looks to drive at it but gets completely undone by the lack of bounce on that occasion.
FOUR! The runs are starting to flow here for Bangladesh and these are vital runs for them. Good length, around off. Das stays back and just caresses it past point for a boundary.
Length again, on off. Das flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Around the off stump, Das blocks it out.
Fuller in length, a bit wider. Das plays it out with soft hands towards covers and picks up a single.
Flighted delivery, on middle and leg. Das defends it back to the bowl.
Flatter and a bit quicker, angled into the leg pole. Litton Das just about manages to work it towards mid-wicket. Das does get the single as well.
Tossed up, around off. Shakib Al Hasan leans in and drives it towards mid on for a single.
Tossed up, full and on the pads. Litton Das eases it past the man at mid on and picks up a couple of runs.
This is floated up, on a length and outside off. Das lets it through to the keeper.
Looped up, on middle. Blocked out.
Back of a length, close to the off stump. Shakib Al Hasan hangs back and taps it towards point for one.
A bit fuller, on middle. Solidly defended out by Das.
FOUR! Gorgeous! Fernando serves a half-volley outside off, Litton Das leans into it and creams it through extra cover for a boundary. Bangladesh trail by just 48 runs now.
Better from Fernando, just back of a length and on off. Das defends it out.
Sloppy! Length ball, around off. Litton Das taps it towards covers where two fielders go for the ball but both end up missing it. This allows Das to pick up a single.
FOUR! Good delivery but it's another boundary for Bangladesh. Fernando goes short and at the body, Shakib Al Hasan awkwardly fends it away and the ball goes off the hips to the fine leg fence.
Flatter delivery, on off. This is worked away in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Jayawickrama sees Shakib Al Hasan advancing and drops it short. Shakib nudges it towards cover-point and once again there's no urgency from the fielders, allowing another easy single.
This is drifted down the leg side, left alone.
Ouch, that must have stung! Very full and on middle, Litton Das backs away and drives it straight into the body of the man at silly point. Oshada Fernando gets hit from close range but he is okay.
On off, blocked off.
Nicely bowled! Flighted delivery, around off. Jayawickrama gives it a good rip and the ball turns and bounces. Litton Das pads out and leaves it alone.

Asitha Fernando hits the deck hard, and serves it around middle. Shakib Al Hasan swivels and pulls it in the gap between deep mid-wicket and deep square leg. The fielder from deep mid-wicket stops the ball, slides, and throws it away from the fielder at deep square leg who was also running for the ball. This little fumble allows the batter to complete three runs.
On a length, around off. There is that uneven bounce again. Litton Das does well to bring his bat down at the right time to block it,
Angling in onto the pads, on a length. Litton Das flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Asitha Fernando drops it short, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan sways away from it.
Back of a length, down the leg side. Shakib Al Hasan pulls it down to deep fine leg for a single.
On a length, around off. Litton Das taps it towards cover-point.
Gives it a nice loop, serves it very full, around middle. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.
Another tossed up delivery, full, around middle. Shakib Al Hasan tucks it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Poor delivery and punished! Short and outside off. Shakib Al Hasan hangs back and punches it through cover for a boundary.
These are easy runs for Bangladesh! Short and outside off again. Shakib Al Hasan pushes it off the back foot through cover. Single taken!
Turning in around middle and leg, shorter ball. Litton Das nudges it through mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Much better from Praveen Jayawickrama! He goes 'round the wicket now, serves a fuller ball, around middle and leg. Shakib Al Hasan steps down the pitch and pushes it back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, shorter in length. Litton Das helps it down to deep fine leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, darting it on thigh pads. Shakib Al Hasan pulls it towards deep square leg. Single taken!
Tighter line from Asitha Fernando now! Back of a length, around the fourth stump line. Litton Das hangs back and blocks it out.
Length delivery, on the pads again. Litton Das flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for an easy single.
Asitha Fernando digs it short, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan defends it out off the back foot.
Another short delivery from 'round the wicket, angling down the leg side. Shakib Al Hasan lets that go through to the keeper.
Tosses it up nicely, fuller ball, around off. Litton Das presses forward and blocks it out.
Gives it a nice loop again, pitches it up, around middle. Litton Das is solid in his front foot defense.

A huge shout for LBW, but not given! This one comes in with the angle, loopy ball, darting it on the pads. Litton Das lunges forward to defend this but he misses and gets rapped on his pad. No review taken that was probably sliding down leg.
Around middle and leg, shorter ball. Litton Das tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Turning in, around middle and leg. Shakib Al Hasan taps it off the back foot towards square leg.
Flighted delivery, full, on middle. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out solidly.
Ramesh Mendis starts with a full ball, around off. Litton Das defends it out watchfully off the front foot.
Turn and bounce! A shorter ball, spinning in sharply, around middle. Litton Das stays in the crease and tries to flick this away, but misses due to some extra bounce.
Fuller, around middle and leg. Litton Das tucks it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Floats it up now, full, around middle. Litton Das leans forward and defends it out.
Fuller ball, around middle and leg. Litton Das flicks it past mid-wicket for a single.
Goes 'round the wicket now, serves a fuller ball, around middle. Shakib Al Hasan defends it watchfully.
Well fielded! Not the best delivery though! Short and wide of off. Litton Das pushes it towards point. The fielder there dives to his left and makes a good stop.
Another shortish ball, around off. Litton Das pushes it off the back foot towards deep cover for a brace.
Back of a length, around off. Litton Das blocks it from within his crease.
Loopy delivery now, outside off, fuller ball. Litton Das leaves it alone.
Another tossed up delivery, down the leg side. Litton Das looks to tuck this away, but he misses.
Tosses it up nicely, very full, around off. Litton Das drives it towards mid off.
Darting it on the pads, very full. Shakib Al Hasan tucks it towards fine leg for a brace.
Shortish ball, around middle, stays low once again. Shakib Al Hasan hangs back and gets his bat down in time to defend this one.
Shorter in length, spinning away, around off. Shakib Al Hasan pushes it off the back foot towards the fielder at point.
Around off, back of a length. Shakib Al Hasan defends it out.
Tad fuller now, around middle and off. Shakib Al Hasan strides forward and defends this one.
The uneven bounce one again! Shorter ball, around middle. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out off the back foot.
Spinning away, outside off, shorter ball. Litton Das pushes it off the back foot towards deep cover. Single taken!
Cheeky from Shakib Al Hasan! Outside off, shorter ball. Shakib Al Hasan stays in his crease, opens the face of the bat, and guides it down to third man. Two taken this time.
Fuller ball, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan gets down on his knee and sweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Tosses it up, very full, around middle. Litton Das defends it out off the front foot.

Back of a length, outside off. Litton Das punches it off the back foot through cover for a single. That will be 2000 Test runs for Litton Das! He becomes the third-quickest player in terms of innings from Bangladesh to do so.
Fuller, around middle. Shakib Al Hasan advances down the pitch and pushes it back to Praveen Jayawickrama.
Quicker through the air, fuller ball, around middle. Litton Das defends this one.
Very full, around middle. Litton Das knocks it down to long on for a single.
A low full toss, around off. Shakib Al Hasan advances down the track and drives it towards deep cover for an easy single.
Much straighter from Ramesh Mendis, outside off. Litton Das leaves it alone.
Very full, around off. Litton Das drives it to the fielder at mid off.
Quicker, fuller, around off. Litton Das solidly defends this one.
Fuller ball, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan dances down the pitch and gently taps it towards cover and takes a single.
Tosses it up, very full, around off. Litton Das drives it towards sweeper cover for another single.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Short and wide of off. Shakib Al Hasan cuts that hard towards the deep cover fence for a boundary. Poor from Praveen Jayawickrama!
Much better! Fuller ball, tad quicker, around middle and leg. Shakib Al Hasan steps down and blocks it out.
A low full toss, around middle and leg. Shakib Al Hasan flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single. Runs continue to flow for Bangladesh!
Tosses it up, very full on this occasion, around middle. Litton Das digs it out. Bangladesh now trails by only 7 runs!
This is angled into the pads from around the wicket. Shakib Al Hasan goes deep in his crease to block it out.
Full toss from Mendis, on off. Shakib pushes it past the diving bowler for an easy single.
Fuller and on middle, flicked away to short mid-wicket.

Huge appeal from the bowler but the skipper asks if it was a bit too high. This is tossed up, well outside off and there's huge turn on offer this time. Litton Das pads it away but very difficult to give that one out. The replay shows that there was a turn and bounce as well, going over the off stump.
On off, defended off the front foot.
On a length, turning in from around off. Litton Das watchfully keeps it out on the leg side.
Use of the feet again from Shakib Al Hasan. This is shorter, on off. Shakib steps out and pushes it towards the vacant mid off region for an easy single.
Tossed up, on off. Das blocks it out.
On the shorter side from Jayawickrama, Litton Das rocks back and punches it through wide mid on for a single.
Slowed up, down the leg side. Shakib nudges it towards backward square leg for one more. Bangladesh trail by just 3 runs now.
Nicely floated up, wide outside off and the ball turns away sharply. Litton Das leaves it alone.
Fuller and around off, stroked away towards covers.
Quicker delivery, darted into middle and leg. Shakib Al Hasan defends it out from inside the crease.
Almost! Quicker again, angled into off. Shakib Al Hasan has a tentative push at it and gets an outside edge that lands in front of the fielder at second slip.
Flatter delivery, around off. Shakib cuts it towards cover-point for a single.
This is a bit wider of the off stump, Litton Das pads it away but he is down in some pain. The replay shows that the ball hit him just above the knee and that's a bit painful.
On the shorter side from Mendis, around off. This one keeps a bit low but Das deals with it well.
Mendis fires it in quicker and on off stump. Litton Das blocks it out. Much better over from Ramesh Mendis.

Starts off with a beauty! Nicely floated up, outside off. The ball hits the rough and just turns away sharply. Shakib Al Hasan gets beaten past the outside edge and Niroshan Dickwella from behind the stumps asks Dhananjaya de Silva where he was all this time.
Around off, pushed away with the spin towards extra cover for a single.
Fuller and on middle, driven down to long on for one more. The Sri Lankan lead is now cancelled out.
On middle, Shakib keeps it out.
Uppish but safe! Tossed up, around off. Shakib Al Hasan gets drawn into the drive and does so uppishly. He gets it down to long off and picks up a single. Bangladesh now lead by 1 run!
Flighted, very full and around off. Litton Das strokes it through extra cover and picks up a couple of runs.
Flatter, just sliding into leg stump. Shakib Al Hasan watchfully keeps it out.
Shakib Al Hasan steps out and Ramesh Mendis fires it in at the toeas. Shakib pushes it out towards covers.
On middle, blocked out.
Use of the feet again from Shakib and Mendis just darts it in. Shakib keeps it out.
Drifting onto the pads, Shakib Al Hasan turns it leg side.
Maiden over! Flatter delivery, close to the off stump. Shakib backs away to cut but taps it towards short third man.
On a nagging length, around off. Litton Das goes on the back foot to defend it out.
On a length, Dhananjaya de Silva gives it a bit more air. Das hangs back and tucks it through square leg for one.
Dhananjaya de Silva pauses before just pushing this one quicker and into the off stump. Shakib Al Hasan just about manages to keep it out.
On middle, nudged away onto the leg side.
Nicely bowled! Drifted into middle, just a hint of turn away. Shakib Al Hasan watchfully keeps it out.

FOUR! Juicy full toss from Dhananjaya de Silva to end the session and Shakib Al Hasan just picks it up and flicks it into the mid-wicket fence. Shakib brings up a sensational half-century as well and that will also be Lunch on Day 5!
Mendis starts off with a shortish delivery, outside off. Litton Das hangs back and dabs it towards the gully region for a quick single.
On off, pushed away towards covers for another easy single.
On a length, turning in from well outside off. Litton Das pads it away to the man at first slip.

Yet another FIFTY for Litton Das and what a series he is having! Tossed up on middle, clipped away towards mid-wicket for one and it's a muted celebration from Das. He is just focusing on getting his team to safety here.
Short and wide, tapped away to sweeper cover for a single. The 100-run partnership is up between these two.
On middle, Das blocks it out.
Starts off with a short ball, on leg stump. Shakib Al Hasan swivel-pulls it down to fine leg for just a single.
Pitched up around off, Litton Das stands tall and punches it through extra cover for a couple of runs.
Close! Length ball, jagging back in from around off and the batter just gets hurried on. Litton Das is late on the defensive shot and gets beaten past the outside edge.
Around the top of off, Das defends it under his eyeline.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! It seemed like Sri Lanka would have to pull off something special to get rid of Litton Das and Asitha Fernando has just produced it! This is pitched up on middle, Das looks to drive it straight back past the bowler but just checks his shot in the end. The ball goes a bit uppishly and Fernando just sticks out a right hand while in his followthrough and pouches it out of thin air. Das departs after another well-made fifty but the visitors have the breakthrough they were looking for. This could be a big turning point in the game.
Howout: c & b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: On a good length over middle, Hossain keeps it down on the leg side.
Nicely drifted into middle, Shakib Al Hasan keeps it out off the back foot.
Sri Lanka turning on the pressure now. On a shorter length, close to the off stump. Shakib Al Hasan looks to cut close to the body but gets beaten past the outside edge due to the extra bounce.
Short again, a bit wider. Shakib cuts it off the back foot to deep point for a single.
Nicely tossed up, on off and turning in. Hossain blocks it out.
That's the one that goes straight on. On a length, on middle and just straightening. Hossain hangs on the back foot and edges it down towards gully.
On middle, turning well down the leg side. Good take there from the keeper.
Short delivery, down leg. Shakib looks to pull but gets a bottom edge down to the keeper.
Good-length, on off. Shakib punches it out towards covers for a single.

NOT OUT! Fuller delivery, angling into the pads. Mosaddek Hossain looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Huge appeal from the bowler but it isn't given and Dimuth Karunaratne does take the review for an lbw decision. No spike on UltraEdge. Ball Tracking shows that the impact is in line of the stumps but the ball is missing the leg stump. Hossain survives and Sri Lanka lose a review as well.
A spicy short ball now, around off. Mosaddek Hossain just sways his head away from the line of the ball.
Full and down the leg side, Hossain misses the flick again.
This is pitched up on off. Hossain drives it towards silly mid on.
Quicker, around middle, flatter ball. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.
Fuller now, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan drives it towards deep cover for a single.
Pitches it up, around off. Mosaddek Hossain drives and finds the fielder at mid off.
Tosses it up, slower through the air, full and outside off. Mosaddek Hossain presses forward and defends it out.

FOUR! Glorious! Mosaddek Hossain gets off the mark in style! Another tossed up delivery, outside off, full in length, Mosaddek Hossain leans forward and creams his drive through cover for a beautiful boundary.
Loopy ball, full, around middle and off. Mosaddek Hossain defends it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Asitha Fernando strikes yet again! He gets rid of another set batter. Bangladesh are in a spot of bother now! Asitha Fernando drops it short now, down leg. Shakib Al Hasan swivels and pulls this one. But the ball goes off the top-edge and lobs up towards the gully region. Niroshan Dickwella runs forward towards his right and takes the catch comfortably. There are new batters at the crease now and the Bangladesh fightback could be over pretty soon as they lead by just 22 runs.
Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Asitha Fernando hits the deck hard again, around middle. Taijul Islam ducks underneath it.
A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire says no! A fuller ball now, around the leg pole. Taijul Islam looks to flick this but he misses and gets hit on his pad. That was pitching outside leg.
Another shorter ball, around middle and leg. Taijul Islam ducks under it.
Back of a length, around off. Taijul Islam gets on his toes and blocks it out towards point.
Another short ball, outside off. Taijul Islam hops and defends it out towards point. A wicket-maiden over from Asitha Fernando!
Fuller ball, spinning in, around middle and leg. Mosaddek Hossain tucks it towards square leg.
Loopy ball, full, outside off now. Mosaddek Hossain lunges forward and defends it out.
Turning in, around middle and leg. Mosaddek Hossain uses the depth of his crease and flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Shorter, quicker, around middle and leg. Mosaddek Hossain tucks it towards the fielder at leg slip, who collects the ball on the bounce.
Pitches it up, around off. Mosaddek Hossain presses forward and pushes it to long on for a single.
Ramesh Mendis goes 'round the wicket now, serves a fuller ball, around middle and off. Taijul Islam defends it out solidly off the front foot.
Asitha Fernando drops it short down the leg side. Mosaddek Hossain miscues his pull shot towards fine leg. Single taken!
Good-length delivery, darting it on the thigh pads. Taijul Islam tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Angling in around middle, on a length. Mosaddek Hossain tucks it to mid-wicket.
Shorter, down middle and leg. Mosaddek Hossain ducks under it.
Back of a length, outside off. Mosaddek Hossain pushes it towards deep cover-point for a single.
Asitha Fernando drops it short again, around middle and leg. Taijul Islam ducks underneath it.

OUT! LBW! Ramesh Mendis grabs his first wicket and Bangladesh are now 8 down! A fuller ball, this one lands around middle and and spins a tad into the leg pole. Mosaddek Hossain hangs back tries to pull this away but he misses and gets hit on his pad. A huge shout for LBW and the umpire raises his finger! Mosaddek Hossain reviews it immediately. No bat involved confirms UltraEdge. Ball Tracking indicates three reds and Mosaddek Hossain has to walk back to the hut. Sri Lanka are sensing a win here! First wicket of the match for a Sri Lankan spinner and it is a timely one too.
Howout: lbw b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Fuller ball, around middle and off. Ebadot Hossain leans and blocks it out.
On middle, tad quicker. Ebadot Hossain hangs back, presents the full face of the bat and blocks it out.
An absolute peach! Quicker, fuller, outside off, straighter on this occasion. Ebadot Hossain presses forward to defend this but he gets beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.
Fuller, around off. Ebadot Hossain blocks it out.
Shorter ball, around off. Ebadot Hossain hangs back and tries to defend this but the ball goes off the outside edge along the ground towards point.
Shorter ball, around middle. Taijul Islam ducks under it and leaves it alone.

OUT! LBW! Asitha Fernando gets his five-wicket haul! What a session he has had! Sri Lanka are one wicket away from batting again. A fuller ball, angling away, around middle and off. Taijul Islam looks to block this but he misses and gets hit on his pad. A huge appeal for LBW, and the umpire agrees! Taijul Islam opts for a review. UltraEdge confirms no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows it is the umpire's call on wickets hitting. Taijul Islam walks back!
Howout: lbw b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! Asitha Fernando grabs his 6th wicket of the innings and his 10th wicket of the match. He becomes the second bowler from Sri Lanka to achieve this feat. The first one was Chaminda Vass to do so! Coming to the ball - Asitha Fernando keeps things simple as he serves a fuller ball, swinging in a tad, and attacking the stumps. Khaled Ahmed looks to hoick this towards the leg side but he misses it completely. The ball goes on to knock the stumps over! Bangladesh have been bundled out for 169 runs with a lead of just 28 runs!
Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: Taijul Islam begins with a fuller ball, quicker one, around middle. Oshada Fernando leans to block this but the ball goes off the inside edge towards fine leg for a brace. Sri Lanka are up and running!
Fuller ball, around off. Oshada Fernando presses forward and defends it out.
FOUR! Oshada Fernando shows some aggression straightaway! A fuller ball, around middle. Oshada Fernando gets down on his knee and sweeps it towards deep square leg for a boundary.

A huge shout for LBW, and the umpire says no! Another fuller ball, outside off, turning in a tad . Oshada Fernando once again looks to sweep this but he misses. Mominul Haque opts for a review! UltraEdge shows a slight spike but there is a clear gap as the ball passes through the bat. No bat involved! Ball Tracking shows the impact was outside off and the on-field decision stands.

FOUR! Edgy runs! Fuller again, outside off, hint of away turn. Oshada Fernando leans forward to drive this but the ball goes off the outside edge away from the slip fielder towards third man for a boundary.

SIX! BANG! Oshada Fernando is in a hurry here! Another pitched up delivery, around middle. Oshada Fernando shimmies down the pitch and tonks it over long off for a biggie. 16 runs off the first over and Sri Lanka are 13 runs away.
Fuller ball, around middle. Dimuth Karunaratne pushes it back to the bowler.
Tosses it up, outside off, full in length. Dimuth Karunaratne presses forward and drives it through cover. Tamim Iqbal chases it and keeps the ball away from the boundary ropes. Two taken!
Drifting in around middle and leg, pitched up delivery. Dimuth Karunaratne tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter, quicker, firing it on the pads. Dimuth Karunaratne clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Shakib Al Hasan drops it short now from 'round the wicket, spinning away, around off. Oshada Fernando hangs back and pulls it past mid-wicket for a boundary. Sri Lanka are 6 runs away!
Fuller, around middle. Oshada Fernando defends it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Ebadot Hossain begins with a fuller ball, wide of off. Dimuth Karunaratne lunges forward and drives it past point for a boundary. 2 needed now.
Angling away, fuller ball, wide of off. Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Another fuller ball, shaping away, wide of off. Dimuth Karunaratne lets that go through to the keeper.
Angling in around middle and leg, on a length. Dimuth Karunaratne tucks it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.

Bye! Ebadot Hossain drops it short now, down the leg side. Dimuth Karunaratne leaves it alone. The keeper does well to get his gloves to it but he fails to grab it. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters sneak in a bye. The scores are now level!

There it is! Oshada Fernando hits the winning runs! A fuller ball, outside off. Oshada Fernando drives it through cover and takes a single. Sri Lanka win the match by 10 wickets and seal the series 1-0!
